 108 ops.register_proto_function(
 109     '{}_{}'.format(_TPU_ESTIMATOR, _ITERATIONS_PER_LOOP_VAR),
 110     proto_type=variable_pb2.VariableDef,
 111     to_proto=resource_variable_ops._to_proto_fn,  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 112     from_proto=resource_variable_ops._from_proto_fn)  # pylint: disable=protected-access

 115 def _create_global_step(graph):
 116   graph = graph or ops.get_default_graph()
 117   if training.get_global_step(graph) is not None:
 118     raise ValueError('"global_step" already exists.')
 119   # Create in proper graph and base name_scope.
 120   with graph.as_default() as g, g.name_scope(None):
 121     return variable_scope.get_variable(
 122         ops.GraphKeys.GLOBAL_STEP,
 123         shape=[],
 124         dtype=dtypes.int64,
 125         initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
 126         trainable=False,
 127         use_resource=True,
 128         collections=[ops.GraphKeys.GLOBAL_VARIABLES, ops.GraphKeys.GLOBAL_STEP])
 129 
 130 
 131 def _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop():
 132   """Creates or gets the iterations_per_loop variable.
 133 
 134   In TPUEstimator, the user provided computation, the model_fn, is wrapped
 135   inside a tf.while_loop for peak performance. The iterations of the loop are
 136   specified by this variable, which adjusts its value on the CPU after each TPU
 137   program execution and before the next TPU execution.
 138 
 139   The purpose of using a variable, rather then a constant, is to allow
 140   TPUEstimator adapt the TPU training iterations according to the final steps
 141   specified by users. For example, if the user sets the iterations_per_loop as 4
 142   in TPUConfig and steps as 10 in TPUEstimator.train(), the iterations_per_loop
 143   variable will have the following value before each TPU training.
 144 
 145       - 1-th TPU execution: iterations_per_loop = 4
 146       - 2-th TPU execution: iterations_per_loop = 4
 147       - 3-th TPU execution: iterations_per_loop = 2
 148 
 149   As model_fn increases the global step once per train_op invocation, the global
 150   step is 10 after all TPU executions, matching the steps=10 inputs passed in by
 151   users.
 152 
 153   Returns:
 154     A TF non-trainable resource variable.
 155 
 156   Raises:
 157     RuntimeError: If multi iterations_per_loop variables were found.
 158   """
 159   graph = ops.get_default_graph()
 160   collection_name = '{}_{}'.format(_TPU_ESTIMATOR, _ITERATIONS_PER_LOOP_VAR)
 161   iter_vars = graph.get_collection(collection_name)
 162   if len(iter_vars) == 1:
 163     return iter_vars[0]
 164   elif len(iter_vars) > 1:
 165     raise RuntimeError('Multiple iterations_per_loop_var in collection.')
 166 
 167   with ops.colocate_with(training_util.get_global_step()):
 168     with variable_scope.variable_scope(
 169         _TPU_ESTIMATOR, reuse=variable_scope.AUTO_REUSE):
 170       return variable_scope.get_variable(
 171           _ITERATIONS_PER_LOOP_VAR,
 172           initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
 173           shape=[],
 174           dtype=dtypes.int32,
 175           trainable=False,
 176           collections=[collection_name, ops.GraphKeys.LOCAL_VARIABLES],
 177           use_resource=True)
 178 
 179 
 180 def _sync_variables_ops():
 181   # Gets the variables back from TPU nodes. This means the variables updated
 182   # by TPU will now be *synced* to host memory.
 183   return [
 184       array_ops.check_numerics(v.read_value(),
 185                                'Gradient for %s is NaN' % v.name).op
 186       for v in variables.trainable_variables()
 187   ]

 190 def _increase_eval_step_op(iterations_per_loop):
 191   """Returns an op to increase the eval step for TPU evaluation.
 192 
 193   Args:
 194     iterations_per_loop: Tensor. The number of eval steps running in TPU
 195         system before returning to CPU host for each `Session.run`.
 196 
 197   Returns:
 198     An operation
 199   """
 200   eval_step = evaluation._get_or_create_eval_step()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 201   # Estimator evaluate increases 1 by default. So, we increase the difference.
 202   return state_ops.assign_add(
 203       eval_step,
 204       math_ops.cast(iterations_per_loop - 1, dtype=eval_step.dtype),
 205       use_locking=True)
 206

 208 def _extract_key_names(tensor_or_dict):
 209   if isinstance(tensor_or_dict, dict):
 210     return sorted(tensor_or_dict.keys())
 211   return []

 214 class _SIGNAL(object):
 215   """Signal used to control the thread of infeed/outfeed.
 216 
 217   All preserved signals must be negative numbers. Positive numbers are used to
 218   indicate the number of iterations for next training/evaluation loop.
 219   """
 220   NEXT_BATCH = -1
 221   STOP = -2

 224 class TPUEstimatorSpec(model_fn_lib._TPUEstimatorSpec):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 225   """Ops and objects returned from a `model_fn` and passed to `TPUEstimator`.
 226 
 227   See `EstimatorSpec` for `mode`, `predictions`, `loss`, `train_op`, and
 228   `export_outputs`.
 229 
 230   For evaluation, `eval_metrics `is a tuple of `metric_fn` and `tensors`, where
 231   `metric_fn` runs on CPU to generate metrics and `tensors` represents the
 232   `Tensor`s transferred from TPU system to CPU host and passed to `metric_fn`.
 233   To be precise, TPU evaluation expects a slightly different signature from the
 234   `tf.estimator.Estimator`. While `EstimatorSpec.eval_metric_ops` expects a
 235   dict, `TPUEstimatorSpec.eval_metrics` is a tuple of `metric_fn` and `tensors`.
 236   The `tensors` could be a list of `Tensor`s or dict of names to `Tensor`s. The
 237   `tensors` usually specify the model logits, which are transferred back from
 238   TPU system to CPU host. All tensors must have be batch-major, i.e., the batch
 239   size is the first dimension. Once all tensors are available at CPU host from
 240   all shards, they are concatenated (on CPU) and passed as positional arguments
 241   to the `metric_fn` if `tensors` is list or keyword arguments if `tensors` is
 242   a dict. `metric_fn` takes the `tensors` and returns a dict from metric string
 243   name to the result of calling a metric function, namely a `(metric_tensor,
 244   update_op)` tuple. See `TPUEstimator` for MNIST example how to specify the
 245   `eval_metrics`.
 246 
 247   `scaffold_fn` is a function running on CPU to generate the `Scaffold`. This
 248   function should not capture any Tensors in `model_fn`.
 249 
 250   `host_call` is a tuple of a `function` and a list or dictionary of `tensors`
 251   to pass to that function and returns a list of Tensors. `host_call` currently
 252   works for train() and evaluate(). The Tensors returned by the function is
 253   executed on the CPU on every step, so there is communication overhead when
 254   sending tensors from TPU to CPU. To reduce the overhead, try reducing the
 255   size of the tensors. The `tensors` are concatenated along their major (batch)
 256   dimension, and so must be >= rank 1. The `host_call` is useful for writing
 257   summaries with `tf.contrib.summary.create_file_writer`.
 258   """
 259 
 260   def __new__(cls,
 261               mode,
 262               predictions=None,
 263               loss=None,
 264               train_op=None,
 265               eval_metrics=None,
 266               export_outputs=None,
 267               scaffold_fn=None,
 268               host_call=None,
 269               training_hooks=None,
 270               evaluation_hooks=None,
 271               prediction_hooks=None):
 272     """Creates a validated `TPUEstimatorSpec` instance."""
 273     host_calls = {}
 274     if eval_metrics is not None:
 275       host_calls['eval_metrics'] = eval_metrics
 276     if host_call is not None:
 277       host_calls['host_call'] = host_call
 278     _OutfeedHostCall.validate(host_calls)
 279 
 280     training_hooks = list(training_hooks or [])
 281     evaluation_hooks = list(evaluation_hooks or [])
 282     prediction_hooks = list(prediction_hooks or [])
 283 
 284     for hook in training_hooks + evaluation_hooks + prediction_hooks:
 285       if not isinstance(hook, session_run_hook.SessionRunHook):
 286         raise TypeError(
 287             'All hooks must be SessionRunHook instances, given: {}'.format(
 288                 hook))
 289 
 290     return super(TPUEstimatorSpec, cls).__new__(
 291         cls,
 292         mode=mode,
 293         predictions=predictions,
 294         loss=loss,
 295         train_op=train_op,
 296         eval_metrics=eval_metrics,
 297         export_outputs=export_outputs,
 298         scaffold_fn=scaffold_fn,
 299         host_call=host_call,
 300         training_hooks=training_hooks,
 301         evaluation_hooks=evaluation_hooks,
 302         prediction_hooks=prediction_hooks)
 303 
 304   def as_estimator_spec(self):
 305     """Creates an equivalent `EstimatorSpec` used by CPU train/eval."""
 306     host_calls = {}
 307     if self.eval_metrics is not None:
 308       host_calls['eval_metrics'] = self.eval_metrics
 309     if self.host_call is not None:
 310       host_calls['host_call'] = self.host_call
 311     host_call_ret = _OutfeedHostCall.create_cpu_hostcall(host_calls)
 312     eval_metric_ops = None
 313     if self.eval_metrics is not None:
 314       eval_metric_ops = host_call_ret['eval_metrics']
 315     hooks = None
 316     if self.host_call is not None:
 317       hooks = [_OutfeedHostCallHook(host_call_ret['host_call'])]
 318     hooks = list(hooks or [])
 319     scaffold = self.scaffold_fn() if self.scaffold_fn else None
 320     return model_fn_lib.EstimatorSpec(
 321         mode=self.mode,
 322         predictions=self.predictions,
 323         loss=self.loss,
 324         train_op=self.train_op,
 325         eval_metric_ops=eval_metric_ops,
 326         export_outputs=self.export_outputs,
 327         scaffold=scaffold,
 328         training_hooks=self.training_hooks + hooks,
 329         evaluation_hooks=self.evaluation_hooks + hooks,
 330         prediction_hooks=self.prediction_hooks + hooks)
 331 
 332 
 333 class _OpQueueContext(object):
 334   """Manages work queue and thread for a infeed/outfeed thread."""
 335 
 336   def __init__(self, name, target, args):
 337     self._name = name
 338     self._queue = Queue.Queue()
 339     args = (self,) + args
 340     self._thread = threading.Thread(name=name, target=target, args=args)
 341     self._thread.daemon = True
 342     self._thread.start()
 343 
 344   def stop(self):
 345     self._queue.put(_SIGNAL.STOP)
 346 
 347   def send_next_batch_signal(self, iterations):
 348     self._queue.put(iterations)
 349 
 350   def read_iteration_counts(self):
 351     while True:
 352       iterations = self._queue.get(block=True)
 353       logging.debug('%s read iterations %s', self._name, iterations)
 354       if iterations == _SIGNAL.STOP:
 355         logging.info('%s received shutdown signal, stopping.', self._name)
 356         return
 357       yield iterations
 358 
 359   def join(self):
 360     logging.info('Shutting down %s thread.' % self._name)
 361     self.stop()
 362     self._thread.join()
 363 
 364 
 365 class _OpSignalOnceQueueContext(_OpQueueContext):
 366   """Manages work queue and thread for a infeed/outfeed thread.
 367 
 368   This subclass only signals once.
 369   """
 370 
 371   def __init__(self, name, target, args):
 372     super(_OpSignalOnceQueueContext, self).__init__(name, target, args)
 373     self._has_signaled = False
 374 
 375   def send_next_batch_signal(self, iterations):
 376     if not self._has_signaled:
 377       self._queue.put(iterations)
 378       self._has_signaled = True
 379

 381 class TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHook(session_run_hook.SessionRunHook):
 382   """A Session hook setting up the TPU initialization, infeed, and outfeed.
 383 
 384   This hook does two major things:
 385   1. initialize and shutdown TPU system.
 386   2. launch and join the threads for infeed enqueue and (optional) outfeed
 387      dequeue.
 388   """
 389 
 390   def __init__(self,
 391                ctx,
 392                enqueue_ops,
 393                dequeue_ops,
 394                run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator=True,
 395                rendezvous=None):
 396     self._master_job = ctx.master_job
 397     self._enqueue_ops = enqueue_ops
 398     self._dequeue_ops = dequeue_ops
 399     self._rendezvous = rendezvous
 400 
 401     self._run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator = run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator
 402     self._initial_infeed_sleep_secs = (
 403         ctx.config.tpu_config.initial_infeed_sleep_secs)
 404 
 405     self._feed_error = None
 406     self._finished = False
 407     self._should_initialize_tpu = True
 408 
 409   def begin(self):
 410     logging.info('TPU job name %s', self._master_job)
 411     self._iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
 412     if self._should_initialize_tpu:
 413       self._init_ops = [tpu.initialize_system(job=self._master_job)]
 414       self._finalize_ops = [tpu.shutdown_system(job=self._master_job)]
 415     else:
 416       self._init_ops = []
 417       self._finalize_ops = []
 418 
 419     summary_writer_init_ops = contrib_summary.summary_writer_initializer_op()
 420     self._init_ops.extend(summary_writer_init_ops)
 421     # Get all the writer resources from the initializer, so we know what to
 422     # flush.
 423     for op in summary_writer_init_ops:
 424       self._finalize_ops.append(contrib_summary.flush(writer=op.inputs[0]))
 425 
 426   def _run_infeed(self, queue_ctx, session):
 427     logging.info('Starting infeed thread controller.')
 428     if self._initial_infeed_sleep_secs:
 429       logging.info('Infeed thread sleeping for %d seconds.',
 430                    self._initial_infeed_sleep_secs)
 431       time.sleep(self._initial_infeed_sleep_secs)
 432       logging.info('Infeed thread starting after sleep')
 433 
 434     with self._rendezvous.catch_errors(source='infeed', session=session):
 435       if self._run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator:
 436         for count, steps in enumerate(queue_ctx.read_iteration_counts()):
 437           for i in xrange(steps):
 438             logging.debug('Infeed enqueue for iteration (%d, %d)', count, i)
 439             session.run(self._enqueue_ops)
 440       else:
 441         for _ in queue_ctx.read_iteration_counts():
 442           session.run(self._enqueue_ops)
 443       logging.info('Infeed thread finished, shutting down.')
 444 
 445   def _run_outfeed(self, queue_ctx, session):
 446     logging.info('Starting outfeed thread controller.')
 447     with self._rendezvous.catch_errors(source='outfeed', session=session):
 448       for count, steps in enumerate(queue_ctx.read_iteration_counts()):
 449         for i in xrange(steps):
 450           logging.debug('Outfeed dequeue for iteration (%d, %d)', count, i)
 451           session.run(self._dequeue_ops)
 452       logging.info('Outfeed thread finished, shutting down.')
 453 
 454   def _create_infeed_controller(self, name, target, args):
 455     return _OpQueueContext(name=name, target=target, args=args)
 456 
 457   def after_create_session(self, session, coord):
 458     logging.info('Init TPU system')
 459     start = time.time()
 460     session.run(self._init_ops,
 461                 options=config_pb2.RunOptions(timeout_in_ms=5 * 60 * 1000))
 462     logging.info('Initialized TPU in %d seconds', time.time() - start)
 463 
 464     self._infeed_controller = self._create_infeed_controller(
 465         name='InfeedController', target=self._run_infeed, args=(session,))
 466 
 467     self._outfeed_controller = _OpQueueContext(
 468         name='OutfeedController', target=self._run_outfeed, args=(session,))
 469 
 470   def before_run(self, run_context):
 471     self._feed_error = None
 472 
 473     iterations = run_context.session.run(self._iterations_per_loop_var)
 474 
 475     logging.info('Enqueue next (%d) batch(es) of data to infeed.', iterations)
 476     self._infeed_controller.send_next_batch_signal(iterations)
 477 
 478     logging.info('Dequeue next (%d) batch(es) of data from outfeed.',
 479                  iterations)
 480     self._outfeed_controller.send_next_batch_signal(iterations)
 481 
 482   def end(self, session):
 483     self._finished = True
 484     logging.info('Stop infeed thread controller')
 485     self._infeed_controller.join()
 486     self._rendezvous.record_done('infeed')
 487 
 488     logging.info('Stop output thread controller')
 489     self._outfeed_controller.join()
 490     self._rendezvous.record_done('outfeed')
 491 
 492     logging.info('Shutdown TPU system.')
 493     session.run(self._finalize_ops)
 494

 499     super(TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHookForPrediction, self).__init__(
 500         ctx, enqueue_ops, dequeue_ops, run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator=False,
 501         rendezvous=rendezvous)
 502 
 503   def _create_infeed_controller(self, name, target, args):
 504     return _OpSignalOnceQueueContext(name=name, target=target, args=args)

 506 
 507 class _TPUStopAtStepHook(session_run_hook.SessionRunHook):
 508   """Hook that requests stop at a specified step.
 509 
 510   This hook is similar to the `session_run_hook._StopAfterNEvalsHook` with
 511   following differences for TPU training:
 512 
 513   1. This hook sets the variable for iterations_per_loop, which is used by
 514      `TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHook` to control the iterations for infeed/outfeed.
 515      As the hook execution order is not guaranteed, the variable update is
 516      handled in `after_create_session` and `after_run` as
 517      `TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHook` reads the variable value in `before_run`.
 518 
 519   2. For each training loop (session.run), the global step could be increased
 520      multiple times on TPU. The global step tensor value will be explicitly read
 521      again in `after_run` to ensure the latest value is retrieved to avoid race
 522      condition.
 523   """
 524 
 525   def __init__(self, iterations, num_steps=None, last_step=None):
 526     """Initializes a `StopAtStepHook`.
 527 
 528     Args:
 529       iterations: The number of iterations to run optimizer per training loop.
 530       num_steps: Number of steps to execute.
 531       last_step: Step after which to stop.
 532 
 533     Raises:
 534       ValueError: If one of the arguments is invalid.
 535     """
 536     if num_steps is None and last_step is None:
 537       raise ValueError('One of num_steps or last_step must be specified.')
 538     if num_steps is not None and last_step is not None:
 539       raise ValueError('Only one of num_steps or last_step can be specified.')
 540     self._num_steps = num_steps
 541     self._last_step = last_step
 542     self._iterations = iterations
 543 
 544   def _next_iterations(self, global_step, last_step):
 545     gap = last_step - global_step
 546     return min(gap, self._iterations)
 547 
 548   def begin(self):
 549     self._global_step_tensor = training_util.get_global_step()
 550     if self._global_step_tensor is None:
 551       raise RuntimeError('Global step should be created.')
 552 
 553     self._iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
 554 
 555   def after_create_session(self, session, coord):
 556     global_step = session.run(self._global_step_tensor)
 557     if self._last_step is None:
 558       self._last_step = global_step + self._num_steps
 559 
 560     iterations = self._next_iterations(global_step, self._last_step)
 561 
 562     self._iterations_per_loop_var.load(iterations, session=session)
 563 
 564   def after_run(self, run_context, run_values):
 565     # Global step cannot be retrieved via SessionRunArgs and before_run due to
 566     # race condition.
 567     global_step = run_context.session.run(self._global_step_tensor)
 568     if global_step >= self._last_step:
 569       run_context.request_stop()
 570     else:
 571       iterations = self._next_iterations(global_step, self._last_step)
 572       self._iterations_per_loop_var.load(
 573           iterations, session=run_context.session)
 574 
 575 
 576 class _SetEvalIterationsHook(session_run_hook.SessionRunHook):
 577   """Hook that requests stop at a specified step."""
 578 
 579   def __init__(self, num_steps):
 580     """Initializes a `_SetEvalIterationsHook`.
 581 
 582     Args:
 583       num_steps: Number of steps to execute.
 584     """
 585     self._num_steps = num_steps
 586 
 587   def begin(self):
 588     self._iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
 589 
 590   def after_create_session(self, session, coord):
 591     self._iterations_per_loop_var.load(self._num_steps, session=session)
 592 
 593 
 594 class _StoppingPredictHook(session_run_hook.SessionRunHook):
 595   """Hook that requests stop according to the stopping signal in prediction."""
 596 
 597   def __init__(self, scalar_stopping_signal):
 598     self._scalar_stopping_signal = scalar_stopping_signal
 599 
 600   def begin(self):
 601     self._iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
 602 
 603   def after_create_session(self, session, coord):
 604     # This is not necessary as we do not run infeed enqueue and outfeed dequeue
 605     # in side threads for prediction model. But it makes the
 606     # TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHook prints nice message.
 607     self._iterations_per_loop_var.load(1, session=session)
 608 
 609   def before_run(self, run_context):
 610     return session_run_hook.SessionRunArgs(self._scalar_stopping_signal)
 611 
 612   def after_run(self, run_context, run_values):
 613     _ = run_context
 614     scalar_stopping_signal = run_values.results
 615     if _StopSignals.should_stop(scalar_stopping_signal):
 616       # NOTE(xiejw): In prediction, stopping signals are inserted for each
 617       # batch. And we append one more batch to signal the system it should stop.
 618       # The data flow might look like
 619       #
 620       #  batch   0: images, labels, stop = 0  (user provided)
 621       #  batch   1: images, labels, stop = 0  (user provided)
 622       #  ...
 623       #  batch  99: images, labels, stop = 0  (user provided)
 624       #  batch 100: images, labels, stop = 1  (TPUEstimator appended)
 625       #
 626       # where the final batch (id = 100) is appended by TPUEstimator, so we
 627       # should drop it before returning the predictions to user.
 628       # To achieve that, we throw the OutOfRangeError in after_run. Once
 629       # Monitored Session sees this error in SessionRunHook.after_run, the
 630       # "current" prediction, i.e., batch with id=100, will be discarded
 631       # immediately
 632       raise errors.OutOfRangeError(None, None, 'Stopped by stopping signal.')
 633 
 634 
 635 def generate_per_core_enqueue_ops_fn_for_host(
 636     ctx, input_fn, inputs_structure_recorder, host_device, host_id):
 637   """Generates infeed enqueue ops for per-core input_fn on a single host."""
 638   captured_infeed_queue = _CapturedObject()
 639   tpu_ordinal_function_impl = ctx.tpu_ordinal_function(host_id)
 640 
 641   def enqueue_ops_fn():
 642     """A fn returns enqueue_ops."""
 643     num_cores_per_host = ctx.num_of_cores_per_host
 644     per_host_sharded_inputs = []
 645     for core_ordinal in range(num_cores_per_host):
 646       with ops.name_scope('ordinal_%d' % (core_ordinal)):
 647         user_context = tpu_context.TPUContext(
 648             internal_ctx=ctx,
 649             input_device=host_device,
 650             invocation_index=host_id * ctx.num_of_cores_per_host + core_ordinal
 651         )
 652         inputs = _Inputs.from_input_fn(input_fn(user_context))
 653         if inputs.is_dataset:
 654           raise TypeError(
 655               '`input_fn` returning `Dataset`  is not yet supported in '
 656               'per-Core input pipeline deployment yet. Please set '
 657               'TPUConfig.per_host_input_for_training to True or return '
 658               '`features` and `labels` from `input_fn`')
 659         features, labels = inputs.features_and_labels()
 660 
 661         inputs_structure_recorder.validate_and_record_structure(
 662             features, labels)
 663         flattened_inputs = (
 664             inputs_structure_recorder.flatten_features_and_labels(
 665                 features, labels))
 666         per_host_sharded_inputs.append(flattened_inputs)
 667 
 668     infeed_queue = tpu_feed.InfeedQueue(
 669         number_of_tuple_elements=len(per_host_sharded_inputs[0]))
 670     captured_infeed_queue.capture(infeed_queue)
 671 
 672     per_host_enqueue_ops = infeed_queue.generate_enqueue_ops(
 673         per_host_sharded_inputs, tpu_ordinal_function=tpu_ordinal_function_impl)
 674     return per_host_enqueue_ops
 675 
 676   return enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue
 677 
 678 
 679 def generate_per_host_enqueue_ops_fn_for_host(
 680     ctx, input_fn, inputs_structure_recorder, batch_axis, device, host_id):
 681   """Generates infeed enqueue ops for per-host input_fn on a single host."""
 682   captured_infeed_queue = _CapturedObject()
 683 
 684   dataset_initializer = None
 685 
 686   with ops.device(device):
 687     user_context = tpu_context.TPUContext(
 688         internal_ctx=ctx,
 689         input_device=device,
 690         invocation_index=host_id)
 691     inputs = _Inputs.from_input_fn(input_fn(user_context))
 692 
 693     is_dataset = inputs.is_dataset
 694     if ctx.mode == model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT:
 695       if not is_dataset:
 696         raise TypeError(
 697             'For mode PREDICT, `input_fn` must return `Dataset` instead of '
 698             '`features` and `labels`.')
 699       if batch_axis is not None:
 700         raise TypeError('For mode PREDICT, batch_axis is not supported yet.')
 701       inputs = _InputsWithStoppingSignals(
 702           dataset=inputs.dataset, batch_size=ctx.batch_size_for_input_fn,
 703           add_padding=True)
 704 
 705     if is_dataset:
 706       dataset_initializer = inputs.dataset_initializer()
 707 
 708     tpu_ordinal_function_impl = ctx.tpu_ordinal_function(host_id)
 709 
 710   def enqueue_ops_fn():
 711     """A Fn returning the TPU infeed enqueue ops.
 712 
 713     By providing as a Fn, it can be invoked inside the tf.while_loop such that
 714     the input pipeline for multiple iterations can be executed by one
 715     Session.run call.
 716 
 717     Returns:
 718       list of dict of ops.
 719     """
 720     with ops.device(device):
 721       num_of_replicas_per_host = ctx.num_of_replicas_per_host
 722       # Convert user input to features and labels.  If the user returns a
 723       # dataset, it is initialized and the features and labels extracted via
 724       # `dataset.iterator.get_next()`
 725       features, labels = inputs.features_and_labels()
 726       signals = inputs.signals()
 727 
 728       inputs_structure_recorder.validate_and_record_structure(features, labels)
 729       unsharded_tensor_list = (
 730           inputs_structure_recorder.flatten_features_and_labels(
 731               features, labels, signals))
 732 
 733       infeed_queue = tpu_feed.InfeedQueue(
 734           tuple_types=[t.dtype for t in unsharded_tensor_list],
 735           tuple_shapes=[t.shape for t in unsharded_tensor_list],
 736           shard_dimensions=batch_axis)
 737       captured_infeed_queue.capture(infeed_queue)
 738       infeed_queue.set_number_of_shards(num_of_replicas_per_host)
 739       per_host_enqueue_ops = (
 740           infeed_queue.split_inputs_and_generate_enqueue_ops(
 741               unsharded_tensor_list,
 742               placement_function=lambda x: device,
 743               tpu_ordinal_function=tpu_ordinal_function_impl))
 744       if signals is None:
 745         return per_host_enqueue_ops
 746       else:
 747         return {
 748             'ops': per_host_enqueue_ops,
 749             'signals': signals,
 750         }
 751 
 752   return enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue, dataset_initializer
 753 
 754 
 755 def generate_per_host_v2_enqueue_ops_fn_for_host(
 756     ctx, input_fn, inputs_structure_recorder, device, host_id):
 757   """Generates infeed enqueue ops for per-host input_fn on a single host."""
 758   captured_infeed_queue = _CapturedObject()
 759   dataset_initializer = None
 760 
 761   with ops.device(device):
 762     user_context = tpu_context.TPUContext(
 763         internal_ctx=ctx,
 764         input_device=device,
 765         invocation_index=host_id)
 766     inputs = _Inputs.from_input_fn(input_fn(user_context))
 767 
 768     is_dataset = inputs.is_dataset
 769     if not is_dataset:
 770       raise TypeError('`input_fn` must return a `Dataset` for the PER_HOST_V2 '
 771                       'input pipeline configuration.')
 772 
 773     if ctx.mode == model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT:
 774       inputs = _InputsWithStoppingSignals(
 775           dataset=inputs.dataset,
 776           batch_size=ctx.batch_size_for_input_fn,
 777           add_padding=True,
 778           num_invocations_per_step=ctx.num_of_replicas_per_host)
 779 
 780     dataset_initializer = inputs.dataset_initializer()
 781     tpu_ordinal_function_impl = ctx.tpu_ordinal_function(host_id)
 782 
 783   def enqueue_ops_fn():
 784     """Generates the per_host enqueue ops."""
 785     control_deps = []
 786     per_host_sharded_inputs = []
 787     num_replicas_per_host = ctx.num_of_replicas_per_host
 788     cached_signals = None
 789     with ops.device(device):
 790       if not inputs.is_dataset:
 791         raise TypeError('`input_fn` must return a `Dataset` for this mode.')
 792       for _ in range(num_replicas_per_host):
 793         # Use control dependencies to ensure a deterministic ordering.
 794         with ops.control_dependencies(control_deps):
 795           features, labels = inputs.features_and_labels()  # Calls get_next()
 796           signals = inputs.signals()
 797 
 798           # All the replicas share the replica 0's stopping singal.
 799           # This avoids inconsistent state among different model replcias.
 800           if cached_signals:
 801             signals['stopping'] = cached_signals['stopping']
 802           else:
 803             cached_signals = signals
 804 
 805         inputs_structure_recorder.validate_and_record_structure(
 806             features, labels)
 807         flattened_inputs = (
 808             inputs_structure_recorder.flatten_features_and_labels(
 809                 features, labels, signals))
 810         control_deps.extend(flattened_inputs)
 811         per_host_sharded_inputs.append(flattened_inputs)
 812 
 813       if inputs_structure_recorder.flattened_input_dims:
 814         input_partition_dims = inputs_structure_recorder.flattened_input_dims
 815         if signals:
 816           input_partition_dims += [None] * len(signals)
 817         # pylint: disable=protected-access
 818         infeed_queue = tpu_feed._PartitionedInfeedQueue(
 819             number_of_tuple_elements=len(per_host_sharded_inputs[0]),
 820             host_id=host_id,
 821             input_partition_dims=input_partition_dims,
 822             device_assignment=ctx.device_assignment)
 823         per_host_enqueue_ops = infeed_queue.generate_enqueue_ops(
 824             per_host_sharded_inputs)
 825       else:
 826         infeed_queue = tpu_feed.InfeedQueue(
 827             number_of_tuple_elements=len(per_host_sharded_inputs[0]))
 828         per_host_enqueue_ops = infeed_queue.generate_enqueue_ops(
 829             per_host_sharded_inputs,
 830             tpu_ordinal_function=tpu_ordinal_function_impl)
 831       captured_infeed_queue.capture(infeed_queue)
 832 
 833     if signals is None:
 834       return per_host_enqueue_ops
 835     else:
 836       return {
 837           'ops': per_host_enqueue_ops,
 838           'signals': signals,
 839       }
 840 
 841   return enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue, dataset_initializer
 842 
 843 
 844 def generate_broadcast_enqueue_ops_fn(ctx, input_fn, inputs_structure_recorder,
 845                                       num_hosts):
 846   """Generates infeed enqueue ops for one input_fn on all the hosts."""
 847   captured_infeed_queue = _CapturedObject()
 848   dataset_initializer = None
 849   device_0 = ctx.tpu_host_placement_function(host_id=0)
 850   with ops.device(device_0):
 851     user_context = tpu_context.TPUContext(
 852         internal_ctx=ctx, input_device=device_0, invocation_index=0)
 853     inputs = _Inputs.from_input_fn(input_fn(user_context))
 854 
 855     is_dataset = inputs.is_dataset
 856     if ctx.mode == model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT:
 857       if not is_dataset:
 858         raise TypeError(
 859             'For mode PREDICT, `input_fn` must return `Dataset` instead of '
 860             '`features` and `labels`.')
 861 
 862       inputs = _InputsWithStoppingSignals(
 863           dataset=inputs.dataset,
 864           batch_size=ctx.batch_size_for_input_fn,
 865           add_padding=True)
 866 
 867     if is_dataset:
 868       dataset_initializer = inputs.dataset_initializer()
 869     num_replicas_per_host = ctx.num_of_replicas_per_host
 870 
 871   def tpu_ordinal_function_impl(replica_id):
 872     if ctx.device_assignment:
 873       return ctx.device_assignment.tpu_ordinal(replica=replica_id)
 874     else:
 875       return replica_id % num_replicas_per_host
 876 
 877   def device_function_impl(replica_id):
 878     return ctx.tpu_host_placement_function(replica_id=replica_id)
 879 
 880   def enqueue_ops_fn():
 881     """Generates enqueue ops for all the hosts."""
 882     broadcasted_inputs = []
 883     flattened_inputs = None  # Cache result from input_fn.
 884     signals = None
 885     for host_id in xrange(num_hosts):
 886       with ops.device(ctx.tpu_host_placement_function(host_id=host_id)):
 887         for _ in xrange(ctx.num_of_replicas_per_host):
 888           # Note: input_fn is only called once at host 0 for the first replica.
 889           # The features and labels returned from that invocation are
 890           # broadcasted to other replicas(including the replicas on other
 891           # hosts).
 892           if flattened_inputs is None:
 893             features, labels = inputs.features_and_labels()  # Calls get_next()
 894             signals = inputs.signals()
 895 
 896             inputs_structure_recorder.validate_and_record_structure(
 897                 features, labels)
 898             flattened_inputs = (
 899                 inputs_structure_recorder.flatten_features_and_labels(
 900                     features, labels, signals))
 901           broadcasted_inputs.append(flattened_inputs)
 902 
 903     infeed_queue = tpu_feed.InfeedQueue(
 904         number_of_tuple_elements=len(broadcasted_inputs[0]))
 905     captured_infeed_queue.capture(infeed_queue)
 906     enqueue_ops = infeed_queue.generate_enqueue_ops(
 907         broadcasted_inputs,
 908         tpu_ordinal_function=tpu_ordinal_function_impl,
 909         placement_function=device_function_impl)
 910 
 911     if signals is None:
 912       return enqueue_ops
 913     else:
 914       return {
 915           'ops': enqueue_ops,
 916           'signals': signals,
 917       }
 918 
 919   return enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue, dataset_initializer
 920 
 921 
 922 class _InputPipeline(object):
 923   """`_InputPipeline` handles invoking `input_fn` and piping to infeed queue.
 924 
 925   `_InputPipeline` abstracts the per-core/per-host `input_fn` invocation from
 926   call site.  To be precise, based on the configuration in
 927   `_InternalTPUContext`,  it invokes `input_fn` for all cores (usually
 928   multi-host TPU training) or for one host (usually for single-host TPU
 929   evaluation), and sends all `features` and `labels` returned by `input_fn` to
 930   TPU infeed. For per-core invocation, `features` and `labels` are piped to
 931   infeed directly, one tuple for each core. For per-host invocation,  `features`
 932   and `labels` are split at host (with respect to `batch_axis`) and piped to all
 933   cores accordingly.
 934 
 935   In addition, flatten/unflatten are handled by `_InputPipeline` also.  Model
 936   inputs returned by the `input_fn` can have one of the following forms:
 937   1. features
 938   2. (features, labels)
 939   3. ((arbitrarily nested structure of features), labels)
 940 
 941   Internally, form 1 is reformed to `(features, None)` as features and labels
 942   are passed separately to underlying methods. For TPU training, TPUEstimator
 943   may expect multiple `features` and `labels` tuples one for each core.
 944 
 945   TPUEstimator allows various different structures for inputs (namely `features`
 946   and `labels`).  `features` can be `Tensor`, dict of string name to `Tensor`,
 947   or nested tuples and `labels` could be `None`, `Tensor`, or dict of string
 948   name to `Tensor`. TPU infeed/outfeed library expects flattened tensor list.
 949   So, `features` and `labels` need to be flattened, before infeed enqueue, and
 950   the structure of them needs to be recorded, in order to restore them after
 951   infeed dequeue.
 952   """
 953 
 954   class InputsStructureRecorder(object):
 955     """The recorder to record inputs structure."""
 956 
 957     def __init__(self, input_partition_dims=None):
 958       # Holds the structure of inputs
 959       self._feature_structure = {}
 960       self._flattened_input_dims = None
 961 
 962       if input_partition_dims:
 963         # This should have been validated in TPUConfig.
 964         assert len(input_partition_dims) <= 2, 'must have 1 or 2 elements.'
 965         if len(input_partition_dims) == 2:
 966           self._feature_dims, self._label_dims = input_partition_dims
 967         else:
 968           self._feature_dims = input_partition_dims[0]
 969           self._label_dims = None
 970 
 971         assert self._feature_dims is not None, ('input_partition_dims[0] must '
 972                                                 'not be None')
 973       else:
 974         self._feature_dims = None
 975         self._label_dims = None
 976 
 977       # Internal state.
 978       self._initialized = False
 979 
 980     @property
 981     def flattened_input_dims(self):
 982       assert self._initialized, 'InputsStructureRecorder is not initialized.'
 983       return self._flattened_input_dims
 984 
 985     def has_labels(self):
 986       return 'labels' in self._feature_structure
 987 
 988     def _flatten_input_dims(self, feature_dims, feature_dims_names, label_dims,
 989                             label_dims_names, label_names, has_labels):
 990       """Flatten input dims with the same order as flattened input tensors."""
 991       flattened_input_dims = []
 992       if feature_dims_names:
 993         # We need a fixed ordering for matching the tensors in features.
 994         flattened_input_dims.extend(
 995             [feature_dims[name] for name in feature_dims_names])
 996       else:
 997         flattened_input_dims.append(feature_dims)
 998 
 999       if label_dims_names:
1000         # We need a fixed ordering for matching the tensors in labels.
1001         flattened_input_dims.extend(
1002             [label_dims[name] for name in label_dims_names])
1003       else:
1004         if label_names:
1005           num_tensors_in_label = len(label_names)
1006         else:
1007           num_tensors_in_label = int(has_labels)
1008         # Setting `None` in input_partition_dims[1] will apply `None` to
1009         # all the tensors in labels, regardless of internal structure.
1010         flattened_input_dims.extend([label_dims] * num_tensors_in_label)
1011 
1012       return flattened_input_dims
1013 
1014     def validate_and_record_structure(self, features, labels):
1015       """Validates and records the structure of `features` and `labels`."""
1016       # Extract structure.
1017       has_labels = labels is not None
1018       feature_names = _extract_key_names(features)
1019       label_names = _extract_key_names(labels)
1020 
1021       if not self._initialized:
1022         # Record structure.
1023         self._initialized = True
1024         if self._feature_dims is not None:
1025           feature_dims_names = _extract_key_names(self._feature_dims)
1026           if feature_dims_names != feature_names:
1027             raise ValueError(
1028                 'TPUConfig.input_partition_dims[0] mismatched feature'
1029                 ' keys. Expected {}, got {}'.format(feature_names,
1030                                                     feature_dims_names))
1031 
1032           label_dims_names = _extract_key_names(self._label_dims)
1033           if self._label_dims is not None and label_dims_names != label_names:
1034             raise ValueError(
1035                 'TPUConfig.input_partition_dims[1] mismatched label'
1036                 ' keys. Expected {}, got {}'.format(label_names,
1037                                                     label_dims_names))
1038 
1039           self._flattened_input_dims = self._flatten_input_dims(
1040               self._feature_dims, feature_dims_names, self._label_dims,
1041               label_dims_names, label_names, has_labels)
1042 
1043     def flatten_features_and_labels(self, features, labels, signals=None):
1044       """Flattens the `features` and `labels` to a single tensor list."""
1045       self._feature_structure['features'] = features
1046       if labels is not None:
1047         self._feature_structure['labels'] = labels
1048       if signals is not None:
1049         self._feature_structure['signals'] = signals
1050       return data_nest.flatten(self._feature_structure)
1051 
1052     def unflatten_features_and_labels(self, flattened_inputs):
1053       """Restores the flattened inputs to original features and labels form.
1054 
1055       Args:
1056         flattened_inputs: Flattened inputs for each shard.
1057 
1058       Returns:
1059         A tuple of (`features`, `labels`), where `labels` could be None.
1060         Each one, if present, should have identical structure (single tensor vs
1061         dict) as the one returned by input_fn.
1062 
1063       Raises:
1064         ValueError: If the number of expected tensors from `flattened_inputs`
1065           mismatches the recorded structure.
1066       """
1067 
1068       unflattened_inputs = data_nest.pack_sequence_as(self._feature_structure,
1069                                                       flattened_inputs)
1070       return _Inputs(
1071           unflattened_inputs['features'],
1072           unflattened_inputs.get('labels'),
1073           signals=unflattened_inputs.get('signals'))
1074 
1075   def __init__(self, input_fn, batch_axis, ctx):
1076     """Constructor.
1077 
1078     Args:
1079       input_fn: input fn for train or eval.
1080       batch_axis: A python tuple of int values describing how each tensor
1081         produced by the Estimator `input_fn` should be split across the TPU
1082         compute shards.
1083       ctx: A `_InternalTPUContext` instance with mode.
1084 
1085     Raises:
1086       ValueError: If both `sharded_features` and `num_cores` are `None`.
1087     """
1088     self._inputs_structure_recorder = _InputPipeline.InputsStructureRecorder(
1089         ctx.input_partition_dims)
1090 
1091     self._sharded_per_core = ctx.is_input_sharded_per_core()
1092     self._input_fn = input_fn
1093     self._infeed_queue = None
1094     self._ctx = ctx
1095     self._batch_axis = batch_axis
1096 
1097   def generate_infeed_enqueue_ops_and_dequeue_fn(self):
1098     """Generates infeed enqueue ops and dequeue_fn."""
1099     # While tf.while_loop is called, the body function, which invokes
1100     # `enqueue_fn` passed in, is called to construct the graph. So, input_fn
1101     # structure is recorded.
1102     enqueue_ops, all_hooks, run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator = (
1103         self._invoke_input_fn_and_record_structure())
1104 
1105     self._validate_input_pipeline()
1106 
1107     def dequeue_fn():
1108       """dequeue_fn is used by TPU to retrieve the tensors."""
1109       # In the model-parallel case, both the host-side and device-side
1110       # computations must agree on the core on which infeed takes place. We
1111       # choose to perform infeed on logical core 0 of each replica.
1112       values = self._infeed_queue.generate_dequeue_op(tpu_device=0)
1113       # The unflatten process uses the structure information recorded above.
1114       return self._inputs_structure_recorder.unflatten_features_and_labels(
1115           values)
1116 
1117     return (enqueue_ops, dequeue_fn, all_hooks, run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator)
1118 
1119   def _invoke_input_fn_and_record_structure(self):
1120     """Deploys the input pipeline and record input structure."""
1121     enqueue_ops = []
1122     infeed_queues = []
1123     all_dataset_initializers = []
1124     num_hosts = self._ctx.num_hosts
1125     tpu_host_placement_fn = self._ctx.tpu_host_placement_function
1126 
1127     run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator = True
1128 
1129     if self._sharded_per_core:
1130       # Per-Core input pipeline deployment.
1131       # Invoke input pipeline for each core and placed on the corresponding
1132       # host.
1133       for host_id in range(num_hosts):
1134         host_device = tpu_host_placement_fn(host_id=host_id)
1135         with ops.device(host_device):
1136           with ops.name_scope('input_pipeline_task%d' % (host_id)):
1137             enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue = (
1138                 generate_per_core_enqueue_ops_fn_for_host(
1139                     self._ctx, self._input_fn, self._inputs_structure_recorder,
1140                     host_device, host_id))
1141 
1142             if _WRAP_INPUT_FN_INTO_WHILE_LOOP:
1143               run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator = False
1144               enqueue_ops.append(
1145                   _wrap_computation_in_while_loop(
1146                       device=host_device, op_fn=enqueue_ops_fn))
1147             else:
1148               enqueue_ops.append(enqueue_ops_fn())
1149             # Infeed_queue_getter must be called after enqueue_ops_fn is called.
1150             infeed_queues.append(captured_infeed_queue.get())
1151 
1152     elif self._ctx.is_input_broadcast_with_iterators():
1153       # Only calls input_fn in host 0.
1154       host_device = tpu_host_placement_fn(host_id=0)
1155       enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue, dataset_initializer = (
1156           generate_broadcast_enqueue_ops_fn(self._ctx, self._input_fn,
1157                                             self._inputs_structure_recorder,
1158                                             num_hosts))
1159       if dataset_initializer:
1160         all_dataset_initializers.append(dataset_initializer)
1161         run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator = False
1162         wrap_fn = (
1163             _wrap_computation_in_while_loop
1164             if self._ctx.mode != model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT else
1165             _wrap_computation_in_while_loop_with_stopping_signals)
1166         enqueue_ops.append(wrap_fn(device=host_device, op_fn=enqueue_ops_fn))
1167       else:
1168         enqueue_ops.append(enqueue_ops_fn())
1169       infeed_queues.append(captured_infeed_queue.get())
1170     else:
1171       for host_id in range(num_hosts):
1172         host_device = tpu_host_placement_fn(host_id=host_id)
1173         with ops.device(host_device):
1174           with ops.name_scope('input_pipeline_task%d' % (host_id)):
1175             if self._ctx.is_input_per_host_with_iterators():
1176               enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue, dataset_initializer = (
1177                   generate_per_host_v2_enqueue_ops_fn_for_host(
1178                       self._ctx, self._input_fn,
1179                       self._inputs_structure_recorder, host_device, host_id))
1180             else:
1181               enqueue_ops_fn, captured_infeed_queue, dataset_initializer = (
1182                   generate_per_host_enqueue_ops_fn_for_host(
1183                       self._ctx, self._input_fn,
1184                       self._inputs_structure_recorder, self._batch_axis,
1185                       host_device, host_id))
1186 
1187             # NOTE(xiejw): We dispatch here based on the return type of the
1188             # users `input_fn`.
1189             #
1190             # 1. If input_fn returns a Dataset instance, we initialize the
1191             # iterator outside of tf.while_loop, and call the iterator.get_next
1192             # inside tf.while_loop.  This should be always safe.
1193             #
1194             # 2. If input_fn returns (features, labels), it is too late to wrap
1195             # them inside tf.while_loop, as resource initialization cannot be
1196             # handled in TF control flow properly. In this case, we will use
1197             # python loop to enqueue the data into TPU system.  This may be
1198             # slow compared to the previous case.
1199             if dataset_initializer:
1200               all_dataset_initializers.append(dataset_initializer)
1201               run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator = False
1202               wrap_fn = (
1203                   _wrap_computation_in_while_loop
1204                   if self._ctx.mode != model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT else
1205                   _wrap_computation_in_while_loop_with_stopping_signals)
1206               enqueue_ops.append(
1207                   wrap_fn(device=host_device, op_fn=enqueue_ops_fn))
1208             else:
1209               enqueue_ops.append(enqueue_ops_fn())
1210             infeed_queues.append(captured_infeed_queue.get())
1211     # infeed_queue is used to generate dequeue ops. The only thing it uses for
1212     # dequeue is dtypes and types. So, any one can be used. Here, grab the
1213     # first one.
1214     self._infeed_queue = infeed_queues[0]
1215     return enqueue_ops, [
1216         estimator_util.MultiHostDatasetInitializerHook(all_dataset_initializers)
1217     ], run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator
1218 
1219   def _validate_input_pipeline(self):
1220     """Validates the input pipeline.
1221 
1222     Perform some sanity checks to log user friendly information. We should
1223     error out to give users better error message. But, if
1224     _WRAP_INPUT_FN_INTO_WHILE_LOOP is False (legacy behavior), we cannot break
1225     user code, so, log a warning.
1226 
1227     Raises:
1228       RuntimeError: If the validation failed.
1229     """
1230     if ops.get_default_graph().get_collection(ops.GraphKeys.QUEUE_RUNNERS):
1231       err_msg = ('Input pipeline contains one or more QueueRunners. '
1232                  'It could be slow and not scalable. Please consider '
1233                  'converting your input pipeline to use `tf.data` instead (see '
1234                  'https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/datasets for '
1235                  'instructions.')
1236       if _WRAP_INPUT_FN_INTO_WHILE_LOOP:
1237         raise RuntimeError(err_msg)
1238       else:
1239         logging.warn(err_msg)
1240 
1241 
1242 class _ModelFnWrapper(object):
1243   """A `model_fn` wrapper.
1244 
1245   This makes calling model_fn on CPU and TPU easier and more consistent and
1246   performs necessary check and mutation required by TPU training and evaluation.
1247 
1248   In addition, this wrapper manages converting the `model_fn` to a single TPU
1249   train and eval step.
1250   """
1251 
1252   def __init__(self, model_fn, config, params, ctx):
1253     self._model_fn = model_fn
1254     self._config = config
1255     self._params = params
1256     self._ctx = ctx
1257 
1258   def call_without_tpu(self, features, labels, is_export_mode):
1259     return self._call_model_fn(features, labels, is_export_mode=is_export_mode)
1260 
1261   def convert_to_single_tpu_train_step(self, dequeue_fn):
1262     """Converts user provided model_fn` as a single train step on TPU.
1263 
1264     The user provided `model_fn` takes input tuple
1265     (features, labels) and produces the EstimatorSpec with train_op and loss for
1266     train `mode`. This usually represents a single train computation on CPU.
1267 
1268     For TPU training, a train (computation) step is first wrapped in a
1269     tf.while_loop control flow to repeat for many times and then replicated to
1270     all TPU shards. Besides the input should be taken from TPU infeed rather
1271     than input pipeline (input_fn) directly. To fit TPU loop and replicate
1272     pattern, the original train computation should be reformed, which is the
1273     returned `train_step`.
1274 
1275     Args:
1276       dequeue_fn: The function to retrieve inputs, features and labels, from TPU
1277         infeed dequeue channel.
1278 
1279     Returns:
1280       A tuple of train_fn, host_calls, and captured scaffold_fn. The train_fn
1281       representing the train step for TPU.
1282     """
1283 
1284     host_call = _OutfeedHostCall(self._ctx)
1285     captured_scaffold_fn = _CapturedObject()
1286     captured_training_hooks = _CapturedObject()
1287 
1288     def train_step(loss):
1289       """Training step function for use inside a while loop."""
1290       del loss  # unused; required in function signature.
1291       inputs = dequeue_fn()
1292       features, labels = inputs.features_and_labels()
1293 
1294       estimator_spec = self._verify_estimator_spec(
1295           self._call_model_fn(features, labels))
1296       loss, train_op = estimator_spec.loss, estimator_spec.train_op
1297 
1298       if isinstance(estimator_spec, model_fn_lib._TPUEstimatorSpec):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1299         captured_scaffold_fn.capture(estimator_spec.scaffold_fn)
1300       else:
1301         captured_scaffold_fn.capture(None)
1302 
1303       captured_training_hooks.capture(estimator_spec.training_hooks)
1304 
1305       # We must run train_op to update the variables prior to running the
1306       # outfeed.
1307       with ops.control_dependencies([train_op]):
1308         host_call_outfeed_ops = []
1309         if (isinstance(estimator_spec, model_fn_lib._TPUEstimatorSpec)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1310             and estimator_spec.host_call is not None):
1311           host_call.record({'host_call': estimator_spec.host_call})
1312           host_call_outfeed_ops = host_call.create_enqueue_op()
1313         with ops.control_dependencies(host_call_outfeed_ops):
1314           return array_ops.identity(loss)
1315 
1316     return (train_step, host_call, captured_scaffold_fn,
1317             captured_training_hooks)
1318 
1319   def convert_to_single_tpu_eval_step(self, dequeue_fn):
1320     """Converts user provided model_fn` as a single eval step on TPU.
1321 
1322     Similar to training, the user provided `model_fn` takes input tuple
1323     (features, labels) and produces the TPUEstimatorSpec with eval_metrics for
1324     eval `mode`. This usually represents a single evaluation computation on CPU.
1325 
1326     For TPU evaluation, a eval (computation) step is first wrapped in a
1327     tf.while_loop control flow to repeat for many times and then replicated to
1328     all TPU shards. Besides the input and output are slightly different. Input,
1329     features and labels, should be taken from TPU infeed rather than input
1330     pipeline (input_fn) directly. Output is managed in two stages.  First, the
1331     model outputs as the result of evaluation computation, usually model logits,
1332     should be transferred from TPU system to CPU. Then, all model outputs are
1333     concatenated first on CPU and sent to the metric_fn for metrics computation.
1334     To fit TPU evaluation pattern, the original eval computation should be
1335     reformed, which is the returned `eval_step`.
1336 
1337     Args:
1338       dequeue_fn: The function to retrieve inputs, features and labels, from TPU
1339         infeed dequeue channel.
1340 
1341     Returns:
1342       A tuple of eval_fn, host_calls, and captured scaffold_fn. The eval_fn
1343       representing the eval step for TPU.
1344     """
1345     host_calls = _OutfeedHostCall(self._ctx)
1346     captured_scaffold_fn = _CapturedObject()
1347     captured_eval_hooks = _CapturedObject()
1348 
1349     def eval_step(total_loss):
1350       """Evaluation step function for use inside a while loop."""
1351       inputs = dequeue_fn()
1352       features, labels = inputs.features_and_labels()
1353 
1354       tpu_estimator_spec = self._call_model_fn(features, labels)
1355       if not isinstance(tpu_estimator_spec, model_fn_lib._TPUEstimatorSpec):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1356         raise RuntimeError(
1357             'estimator_spec used by TPU evaluation must have type'
1358             '`TPUEstimatorSpec`. Got {}'.format(type(tpu_estimator_spec)))
1359 
1360       loss = tpu_estimator_spec.loss
1361       captured_scaffold_fn.capture(tpu_estimator_spec.scaffold_fn)
1362       captured_eval_hooks.capture(tpu_estimator_spec.evaluation_hooks)
1363 
1364       to_record = {}
1365       if tpu_estimator_spec.eval_metrics:
1366         to_record['eval_metrics'] = tpu_estimator_spec.eval_metrics
1367       if tpu_estimator_spec.host_call is not None:
1368         # We assume that evaluate won't update global step, so we don't wrap
1369         # this host_call.
1370         to_record['host_call'] = tpu_estimator_spec.host_call
1371       host_calls.record(to_record)
1372 
1373       with ops.control_dependencies(host_calls.create_enqueue_op()):
1374         return math_ops.add(total_loss, loss)
1375 
1376     return eval_step, host_calls, captured_scaffold_fn, captured_eval_hooks
1377 
1378   def convert_to_single_tpu_predict_step(self, dequeue_fn):
1379     """Converts user provided model_fn` as a single predict step on TPU.
1380 
1381     Args:
1382       dequeue_fn: The function to retrieve inputs, features and labels, from TPU
1383         infeed dequeue channel.
1384 
1385     Returns:
1386       A tuple of predict_fn, host_calls, and captured scaffold_fn. The
1387       predict_fn representing the predict step for TPU.
1388     """
1389     host_calls = _OutfeedHostCall(self._ctx)
1390     captured_scaffold_fn = _CapturedObject()
1391     captured_predict_hooks = _CapturedObject()
1392 
1393     def predict_step(unused_scalar_stopping_signal):
1394       """Evaluation step function for use inside a while loop."""
1395       inputs = dequeue_fn()
1396       features, labels = inputs.features_and_labels()
1397       stopping_signals = inputs.signals()
1398 
1399       assert stopping_signals is not None, (
1400           'Internal Error: `signals` is missing.')
1401 
1402       tpu_estimator_spec = self._call_model_fn(
1403           features, labels, is_export_mode=False)
1404       if not isinstance(tpu_estimator_spec, model_fn_lib._TPUEstimatorSpec):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1405         raise RuntimeError(
1406             'estimator_spec used by TPU prediction must have type'
1407             '`TPUEstimatorSpec`. Got {}'.format(type(tpu_estimator_spec)))
1408 
1409       self._verify_tpu_spec_predictions(tpu_estimator_spec.predictions)
1410 
1411       captured_scaffold_fn.capture(tpu_estimator_spec.scaffold_fn)
1412       captured_predict_hooks.capture(tpu_estimator_spec.prediction_hooks)
1413       to_record = {}
1414       identity_fn = lambda **kwargs: kwargs
1415       to_record['predictions'] = [identity_fn, tpu_estimator_spec.predictions]
1416       to_record['signals'] = [identity_fn, stopping_signals]
1417       if tpu_estimator_spec.host_call is not None:
1418         to_record['host_call'] = tpu_estimator_spec.host_call
1419       host_calls.record(to_record)
1420 
1421       with ops.control_dependencies(host_calls.create_enqueue_op()):
1422         return _StopSignals.as_scalar_stopping_signal(stopping_signals)
1423 
1424     return (predict_step, host_calls, captured_scaffold_fn,
1425             captured_predict_hooks)
1426 
1427   def _verify_tpu_spec_predictions(self, predictions):
1428     """Validates TPUEstimatorSpec.predictions dict."""
1429     # TODO(xiejw): Adds validation for prediction dictionrary.
1430     # TODO(xiejw): Adds support for single tensor as predictions.
1431     if not isinstance(predictions, dict):
1432       raise TypeError('TPUEstimatorSpec.predictions must be dict of Tensors.')
1433 
1434     for (key, tensor) in predictions.items():
1435       if tensor.shape[0].value is None:
1436         raise ValueError(
1437             'The tensor with key ({}) in TPUEstimatorSpec.predictions has '
1438             'dynamic shape (should be static). Tensor: {}'.format(
1439                 key, tensor))
1440     return predictions
1441 
1442   def _validate_model_features_and_labels(self,
1443                                           features,
1444                                           labels,
1445                                           is_export_mode):
1446     """Validates that the features and labels for the model function are valid.
1447 
1448     A valid features/labels object is the one with:
1449     - Type: Tensor or a dictionary of Tensors
1450     - Static shape if is_export_mode is False.
1451 
1452     Args:
1453       features: the features that would be input to the model function.
1454       labels: the labels that would be input to the model function.
1455       is_export_mode: boolean value specifying if in export mode.
1456 
1457     Raises:
1458       TypeError: If features/labels are not of the correct type.
1459       ValueError: If features/labels have dynamic shape.
1460     """
1461 
1462     def validate(obj, obj_name):
1463       """Helper validate function."""
1464       if not isinstance(obj, ops.Tensor) and not isinstance(obj, dict):
1465         raise TypeError(
1466             'The {} to the model returned by input_fn must be either a Tensor '
1467             'or a dictionary of Tensors. {}: {}'.format(obj_name, obj_name,
1468                                                         obj))
1469       if is_export_mode or self._ctx.is_running_on_cpu(is_export_mode):
1470         return
1471       if isinstance(obj, ops.Tensor):
1472         if not obj.get_shape().is_fully_defined():
1473           raise ValueError(
1474               'The {} to the model returned by input_fn must have static shape.'
1475               ' Tensor: {}'.format(obj_name, obj))
1476       else:
1477         for (key, value) in obj.items():
1478           flattened_tensors = data_nest.flatten(value)
1479           for tensor in flattened_tensors:
1480             if not tensor.get_shape().is_fully_defined():
1481               raise ValueError(
1482                   'The {} to the model returned by input_fn must have static '
1483                   'shape. Key: \'{}\', Tensor: {}'.format(
1484                       obj_name, key, tensor))
1485 
1486     validate(features, 'features')
1487     if labels is not None:
1488       validate(labels, 'labels')
1489 
1490   def _call_model_fn(self, features, labels, is_export_mode=False):
1491     """Calls the model_fn with required parameters."""
1492     self._validate_model_features_and_labels(features, labels, is_export_mode)
1493     model_fn_args = function_utils.fn_args(self._model_fn)
1494     kwargs = {}
1495 
1496     # Makes deep copy with `config` and params` in case user mutates them.
1497     config = copy.deepcopy(self._config)
1498     params = copy.deepcopy(self._params)
1499 
1500     if 'labels' in model_fn_args:
1501       kwargs['labels'] = labels
1502     elif labels is not None:
1503       raise ValueError(
1504           'model_fn does not take labels, but input_fn returns labels.')
1505     if 'mode' in model_fn_args:
1506       kwargs['mode'] = self._ctx.mode
1507     if 'config' in model_fn_args:
1508       kwargs['config'] = config
1509     if 'params' in model_fn_args:
1510       kwargs['params'] = params
1511 
1512     if 'params' not in model_fn_args:
1513       raise ValueError('model_fn ({}) does not include params argument, '
1514                        'required by TPUEstimator to pass batch size as '
1515                        'params[\'batch_size\']'.format(self._model_fn))
1516 
1517     if is_export_mode:
1518       batch_size_for_model_fn = None
1519     else:
1520       batch_size_for_model_fn = self._ctx.batch_size_for_model_fn
1521 
1522     if batch_size_for_model_fn is not None:
1523       _add_item_to_params(params, _BATCH_SIZE_KEY, batch_size_for_model_fn)
1524 
1525     running_on_cpu = self._ctx.is_running_on_cpu(is_export_mode)
1526     _add_item_to_params(params, _USE_TPU_KEY, not running_on_cpu)
1527 
1528     if not running_on_cpu:
1529       user_context = tpu_context.TPUContext(
1530           internal_ctx=self._ctx, call_from_input_fn=False)
1531       _add_item_to_params(params, _CTX_KEY, user_context)
1532 
1533     estimator_spec = self._model_fn(features=features, **kwargs)
1534     if (running_on_cpu and
1535         isinstance(estimator_spec, model_fn_lib._TPUEstimatorSpec)):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1536       # The estimator_spec will be passed to `Estimator` directly, which expects
1537       # type `EstimatorSpec`.
1538       return estimator_spec.as_estimator_spec()
1539     else:
1540       return estimator_spec
1541 
1542   def _verify_estimator_spec(self, estimator_spec):
1543     """Validates the estimator_spec."""
1544     if isinstance(estimator_spec, model_fn_lib._TPUEstimatorSpec):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1545       return estimator_spec
1546 
1547     err_msg = '{} returned by EstimatorSpec is not supported in TPUEstimator.'
1548     if estimator_spec.training_chief_hooks:
1549       raise ValueError(
1550           err_msg.format('training_chief_hooks') + 'If you want' +
1551           ' to pass training hooks, please pass via training_hooks.')
1552 
1553     if estimator_spec.scaffold:
1554       logging.warning('EstimatorSpec.Scaffold is ignored by TPU train/eval. '
1555                       'Please use TPUEstimatorSpec.')
1556     return estimator_spec
1557 
1558 
1559 class _OutfeedHostCall(object):
1560   """Support for `eval_metrics` and `host_call` in TPUEstimatorSpec."""
1561 
1562   def __init__(self, ctx):
1563     self._ctx = ctx
1564     self._names = []
1565     # All of these are dictionaries of lists keyed on the name.
1566     self._host_fns = {}
1567     self._tensor_keys = collections.defaultdict(list)
1568     self._tensors = collections.defaultdict(list)
1569     self._tensor_dtypes = collections.defaultdict(list)
1570     self._tensor_shapes = collections.defaultdict(list)
1571 
1572   @staticmethod
1573   def validate(host_calls):
1574     """Validates the `eval_metrics` and `host_call` in `TPUEstimatorSpec`."""
1575 
1576     for name, host_call in host_calls.items():
1577       if not isinstance(host_call, (tuple, list)):
1578         raise ValueError('{} should be tuple or list'.format(name))
1579       if len(host_call) != 2:
1580         raise ValueError('{} should have two elements.'.format(name))
1581       if not callable(host_call[0]):
1582         raise TypeError('{}[0] should be callable.'.format(name))
1583       if not isinstance(host_call[1], (tuple, list, dict)):
1584         raise ValueError('{}[1] should be tuple or list, or dict.'.format(name))
1585 
1586       if isinstance(host_call[1], (tuple, list)):
1587         fullargspec = tf_inspect.getfullargspec(host_call[0])
1588         fn_args = function_utils.fn_args(host_call[0])
1589         # wrapped_hostcall_with_global_step uses varargs, so we allow that.
1590         if fullargspec.varargs is None and len(host_call[1]) != len(fn_args):
1591           raise RuntimeError(
1592               'In TPUEstimatorSpec.{}, length of tensors {} does not match '
1593               'method args of the function, which takes {}.'.format(
1594                   name, len(host_call[1]), len(fn_args)))
1595 
1596   @staticmethod
1597   def create_cpu_hostcall(host_calls):
1598     """Runs on the host_call on CPU instead of TPU when use_tpu=False."""
1599 
1600     _OutfeedHostCall.validate(host_calls)
1601     ret = {}
1602     for name, host_call in host_calls.items():
1603       host_fn, tensors = host_call
1604       if isinstance(tensors, (tuple, list)):
1605         ret[name] = host_fn(*tensors)
1606       else:
1607         # Must be dict.
1608         try:
1609           ret[name] = host_fn(**tensors)
1610         except TypeError as e:
1611           logging.warning(
1612               'Exception while calling %s: %s. It is likely the tensors '
1613               '(%s[1]) do not match the '
1614               'function\'s arguments', name, e, name)
1615           raise e
1616     return ret
1617 
1618   def record(self, host_calls):
1619     """Records the host_call structure."""
1620 
1621     for name, host_call in host_calls.items():
1622       host_fn, tensor_list_or_dict = host_call
1623       self._names.append(name)
1624       self._host_fns[name] = host_fn
1625 
1626       if isinstance(tensor_list_or_dict, dict):
1627         for (key, tensor) in six.iteritems(tensor_list_or_dict):
1628           self._tensor_keys[name].append(key)
1629           self._tensors[name].append(tensor)
1630           self._tensor_dtypes[name].append(tensor.dtype)
1631           self._tensor_shapes[name].append(tensor.shape)
1632       else:
1633         # List or tuple.
1634         self._tensor_keys[name] = None
1635         for tensor in tensor_list_or_dict:
1636           self._tensors[name].append(tensor)
1637           self._tensor_dtypes[name].append(tensor.dtype)
1638           self._tensor_shapes[name].append(tensor.shape)
1639 
1640   def create_enqueue_op(self):
1641     """Create the op to enqueue the recorded host_calls.
1642 
1643     Returns:
1644       A list of enqueue ops, which is empty if there are no host calls.
1645     """
1646     if not self._names:
1647       return []
1648 
1649     tensors = []
1650     # TODO(jhseu): Consider deduping tensors.
1651     for name in self._names:
1652       tensors.extend(self._tensors[name])
1653 
1654     with ops.device(tpu.core(0)):
1655       return [tpu_ops.outfeed_enqueue_tuple(tensors)]
1656 
1657   def create_tpu_hostcall(self):
1658     """Sends the tensors through outfeed and runs the host_fn on CPU.
1659 
1660     The tensors are concatenated along dimension 0 to form a global tensor
1661     across all shards. The concatenated function is passed to the host_fn and
1662     executed on the first host.
1663 
1664     Returns:
1665       A dictionary mapping name to the return type of the host_call by that
1666       name.
1667 
1668     Raises:
1669       RuntimeError: If outfeed tensor is scalar.
1670     """
1671     if not self._names:
1672       return {}
1673 
1674     ret = {}
1675     # For each i, dequeue_ops[i] is a list containing the tensors from all
1676     # shards. This list is concatenated later.
1677     dequeue_ops = []
1678     tensor_dtypes = []
1679     tensor_shapes = []
1680     for name in self._names:
1681       for _ in self._tensors[name]:
1682         dequeue_ops.append([])
1683       for dtype in self._tensor_dtypes[name]:
1684         tensor_dtypes.append(dtype)
1685       for shape in self._tensor_shapes[name]:
1686         tensor_shapes.append(shape)
1687 
1688     # Outfeed ops execute on each replica's first logical core. Note: we must
1689     # constraint it such that we have at most one outfeed dequeue and enqueue
1690     # per replica.
1691     for i in xrange(self._ctx.num_replicas):
1692       host_device, ordinal_id = self._ctx.device_for_replica(i)
1693       with ops.device(host_device):
1694         outfeed_tensors = tpu_ops.outfeed_dequeue_tuple(
1695             dtypes=tensor_dtypes,
1696             shapes=tensor_shapes,
1697             device_ordinal=ordinal_id)
1698         for j, item in enumerate(outfeed_tensors):
1699           dequeue_ops[j].append(item)
1700 
1701     # Deconstruct dequeue ops.
1702     dequeue_ops_by_name = {}
1703     pos = 0
1704     for name in self._names:
1705       dequeue_ops_by_name[name] = dequeue_ops[pos:pos+len(self._tensors[name])]
1706       pos += len(self._tensors[name])
1707 
1708     # It is assumed evaluation always happens on single host TPU system. So,
1709     # place all ops on tpu host if possible.
1710     #
1711     # TODO(jhseu): Evaluate whether this is right for summaries.
1712     with ops.device(self._ctx.tpu_host_placement_function(replica_id=0)):
1713       for name in self._names:
1714         dequeue_ops = dequeue_ops_by_name[name]
1715         for i, item in enumerate(dequeue_ops):
1716           if dequeue_ops[i][0].shape.ndims == 0:
1717             raise RuntimeError(
1718                 'All tensors outfed from TPU should preserve batch size '
1719                 'dimension, but got scalar {}'.format(dequeue_ops[i][0]))
1720           # TODO(xiejw): Allow users to specify the axis for batch size
1721           # dimension.
1722           dequeue_ops[i] = array_ops.concat(dequeue_ops[i], axis=0)
1723 
1724         if self._tensor_keys[name] is not None:
1725           # The user-provided eval_metrics[1] is a dict.
1726           dequeue_ops = dict(zip(self._tensor_keys[name], dequeue_ops))
1727           try:
1728             ret[name] = self._host_fns[name](**dequeue_ops)
1729           except TypeError as e:
1730             logging.warning(
1731                 'Exception while calling %s: %s. It is likely the tensors '
1732                 '(%s[1]) do not match the '
1733                 'function\'s arguments', name, e, name)
1734             raise e
1735         else:
1736           ret[name] = self._host_fns[name](*dequeue_ops)
1737 
1738     return ret
1739 
1740 
1741 class _OutfeedHostCallHook(session_run_hook.SessionRunHook):
1742   """Hook to run host calls when use_tpu=False."""
1743 
1744   def __init__(self, tensors):
1745     self._tensors = tensors
1746 
1747   def begin(self):
1748     # We duplicate this code from the TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHook rather than
1749     # create a separate hook to guarantee execution order, because summaries
1750     # need to be initialized before the outfeed thread starts.
1751     # TODO(jhseu): Make a wrapper hook instead?
1752     self._init_ops = contrib_summary.summary_writer_initializer_op()
1753     # Get all the writer resources from the initializer, so we know what to
1754     # flush.
1755     self._finalize_ops = []
1756     for op in self._init_ops:
1757       self._finalize_ops.append(contrib_summary.flush(writer=op.inputs[0]))
1758 
1759   def after_create_session(self, session, coord):
1760     session.run(self._init_ops)
1761 
1762   def before_run(self, run_context):
1763     return basic_session_run_hooks.SessionRunArgs(self._tensors)
1764 
1765   def end(self, session):
1766     session.run(self._finalize_ops)

1769 class ExamplesPerSecondHook(basic_session_run_hooks.StepCounterHook):
1770   """Calculate and report global_step/sec and examples/sec during runtime."""
1771 
1772   def __init__(self,
1773                batch_size,
1774                every_n_steps=100,
1775                every_n_secs=None,
1776                output_dir=None,
1777                summary_writer=None):
1778     self._batch_size = batch_size
1779     super(ExamplesPerSecondHook, self).__init__(
1780         every_n_steps=every_n_steps,
1781         every_n_secs=every_n_secs,
1782         output_dir=output_dir,
1783         summary_writer=summary_writer)
1784 
1785   def _log_and_record(self, elapsed_steps, elapsed_time, global_step):
1786     global_step_per_sec = elapsed_steps / elapsed_time
1787     examples_per_sec = self._batch_size * global_step_per_sec
1788     if self._summary_writer is not None:
1789       global_step_summary = Summary(value=[
1790           Summary.Value(tag='global_step/sec', simple_value=global_step_per_sec)
1791       ])
1792       example_summary = Summary(value=[
1793           Summary.Value(tag='examples/sec', simple_value=examples_per_sec)
1794       ])
1795       self._summary_writer.add_summary(global_step_summary, global_step)
1796       self._summary_writer.add_summary(example_summary, global_step)
1797     logging.info('global_step/sec: %g', global_step_per_sec)
1798     logging.info('examples/sec: %g', examples_per_sec)

1801 class InstallSignalHandlerHook(session_run_hook.SessionRunHook):
1802   """Change SIGINT (CTRL^C) handler to force quit the process.
1803 
1804   The default behavior often results in hanging processes.
1805   The original handler is restored after training/evaluation.
1806   """
1807 
1808   def __init__(self):
1809     self._signal_fn = signal.getsignal(signal.SIGINT)
1810 
1811   def before_run(self, run_context):
1812     signal.signal(signal.SIGINT, signal.SIG_DFL)
1813 
1814   def end(self, session):
1815     signal.signal(signal.SIGINT, self._signal_fn)
