1817 
1818 class TPUEstimator(estimator_lib.Estimator):
1819   """Estimator with TPU support.
1820 
1821   TPUEstimator also supports training on CPU and GPU. You don't need to define
1822   a separate `tf.estimator.Estimator`.
1823 
1824   TPUEstimator handles many of the details of running on TPU devices, such as
1825   replicating inputs and models for each core, and returning to host
1826   periodically to run hooks.
1827 
1828   TPUEstimator transforms a global batch size in params to a per-shard batch
1829   size when calling the `input_fn` and `model_fn`. Users should specify
1830   global batch size in constructor, and then get the batch size for each shard
1831   in `input_fn` and `model_fn` by `params['batch_size']`.
1832 
1833   - For training, `model_fn` gets per-core batch size; `input_fn` may get
1834     per-core or per-host batch size depending on `per_host_input_for_training`
1835     in `TPUConfig` (See docstring for TPUConfig for details).
1836 
1837   - For evaluation and prediction, `model_fn` gets per-core batch size and
1838     `input_fn` get per-host batch size.
1839 
1840   Evaluation
1841   ==========
1842 
1843   `model_fn` should return `TPUEstimatorSpec`, which expects the `eval_metrics`
1844   for TPU evaluation. However, if eval_on_tpu is False, `model_fn` must return
1845   `EstimatorSpec` and the evaluation will execute on CPU or GPU; in this case
1846   the following discussion on TPU evaluation does not apply.
1847 
1848   `TPUEstimatorSpec.eval_metrics` is a tuple of `metric_fn` and `tensors`, where
1849   `tensors` could be a list of `Tensor`s or dict of names to `Tensor`s. (See
1850   `TPUEstimatorSpec` for details).  `metric_fn` takes the `tensors` and returns
1851   a dict from metric string name to the result of calling a metric function,
1852   namely a `(metric_tensor, update_op)` tuple.
1853 
1854   One can set `use_tpu` to `False` for testing. All training, evaluation, and
1855   predict will be executed on CPU. `input_fn` and `model_fn` will receive
1856   `train_batch_size` or `eval_batch_size` unmodified as `params['batch_size']`.
1857 
1858   Current limitations:
1859   --------------------
1860 
1861   1. TPU evaluation only works on a single host (one TPU worker) except
1862      BROADCAST mode.
1863 
1864   2. `input_fn` for evaluation should **NOT** raise an end-of-input exception
1865      (`OutOfRangeError` or `StopIteration`). And all evaluation steps and all
1866      batches should have the same size.
1867 
1868   Example (MNIST):
1869   ----------------
1870 
1871   ```
1872   # The metric Fn which runs on CPU.
1873   def metric_fn(labels, logits):
1874     predictions = tf.argmax(logits, 1)
1875     return {
1876       'accuracy': tf.metrics.precision(
1877           labels=labels, predictions=predictions),
1878     }
1879 
1880   # Your model Fn which runs on TPU (eval_metrics is list in this example)
1881   def model_fn(features, labels, mode, config, params):
1882     ...
1883     logits = ...
1884 
1885     if mode = tf.estimator.ModeKeys.EVAL:
1886       return tpu_estimator.TPUEstimatorSpec(
1887           mode=mode,
1888           loss=loss,
1889           eval_metrics=(metric_fn, [labels, logits]))
1890 
1891   # or specify the eval_metrics tensors as dict.
1892   def model_fn(features, labels, mode, config, params):
1893     ...
1894     final_layer_output = ...
1895 
1896     if mode = tf.estimator.ModeKeys.EVAL:
1897       return tpu_estimator.TPUEstimatorSpec(
1898           mode=mode,
1899           loss=loss,
1900           eval_metrics=(metric_fn, {
1901               'labels': labels,
1902               'logits': final_layer_output,
1903           }))
1904   ```
1905 
1906   Prediction
1907   ==========
1908 
1909   Prediction on TPU is an experimental feature to support large batch inference.
1910   It is not designed for latency-critical system. In addition, due to some
1911   usability issues, for prediction with small dataset, CPU `.predict`, i.e.,
1912   creating a new `TPUEstimator` instance with `use_tpu=False`, might be more
1913   convenient.
1914 
1915   Note: In contrast to TPU training/evaluation, the `input_fn` for prediction
1916   *should* raise an end-of-input exception (`OutOfRangeError` or
1917   `StopIteration`), which serves as the stopping signal to `TPUEstimator`. To be
1918   precise, the ops created by `input_fn` produce one batch of the data.
1919   The `predict()` API processes one batch at a time. When reaching the end of
1920   the data source, an end-of-input exception should be raised by one of these
1921   operations. The user usually does not need to do this manually. As long as the
1922   dataset is not repeated forever, the `tf.data` API will raise an end-of-input
1923   exception automatically after the last batch has been produced.
1924 
1925   Note: Estimator.predict returns a Python generator. Please consume all the
1926   data from the generator so that TPUEstimator can shutdown the TPU system
1927   properly for user.
1928 
1929   Current limitations:
1930   --------------------
1931   1. TPU prediction only works on a single host (one TPU worker).
1932 
1933   2. `input_fn` must return a `Dataset` instance rather than `features`. In
1934   fact, .train() and .evaluate() also support Dataset as return value.
1935 
1936   Example (MNIST):
1937   ----------------
1938   ```
1939   height = 32
1940   width = 32
1941   total_examples = 100
1942 
1943   def predict_input_fn(params):
1944     batch_size = params['batch_size']
1945 
1946     images = tf.random_uniform(
1947         [total_examples, height, width, 3], minval=-1, maxval=1)
1948 
1949     dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices(images)
1950     dataset = dataset.map(lambda images: {'image': images})
1951 
1952     dataset = dataset.batch(batch_size)
1953     return dataset
1954 
1955   def model_fn(features, labels, params, mode):
1956      # Generate predictions, called 'output', from features['image']
1957 
1958     if mode == tf.estimator.ModeKeys.PREDICT:
1959       return tf.contrib.tpu.TPUEstimatorSpec(
1960           mode=mode,
1961           predictions={
1962               'predictions': output,
1963               'is_padding': features['is_padding']
1964           })
1965 
1966   tpu_est = TPUEstimator(
1967       model_fn=model_fn,
1968       ...,
1969       predict_batch_size=16)
1970 
1971   # Fully consume the generator so that TPUEstimator can shutdown the TPU
1972   # system.
1973   for item in tpu_est.predict(input_fn=input_fn):
1974     # Filter out item if the `is_padding` is 1.
1975     # Process the 'predictions'
1976   ```
1977 
1978   Exporting
1979   =========
1980 
1981   `export_savedmodel` exports 2 metagraphs, one with `tag_constants.SERVING`,
1982   and another with `tag_constants.SERVING` and `tag_constants.TPU`.
1983   At serving time, these tags are used to select metagraph to load.
1984 
1985   Before running the graph on TPU, TPU system needs to be initialized. If
1986   TensorFlow Serving model-server is used, this is done automatically. If
1987   not, please call `session.run(tpu.initialize_system())`.
1988 
1989   `tpu.outside_compilation` can be used to wrap TPU incompatible ops in
1990   `model_fn`.
1991 
1992   Example:
1993   ----------------
1994 
1995   ```
1996   def model_fn(features, labels, mode, config, params):
1997     ...
1998     logits = ...
1999     export_outputs = {
2000       'logits': export_output_lib.PredictOutput(
2001         {'logits': logits})
2002     }
2003 
2004     def host_call(logits):
2005       class_ids = math_ops.argmax(logits)
2006       classes = string_ops.as_string(class_ids)
2007       export_outputs['classes'] =
2008         export_output_lib.ClassificationOutput(classes=classes)
2009 
2010     tpu.outside_compilation(host_call, logits)
2011 
2012     ...
2013   ```
2014 
2015   """
2016 
2017   def __init__(self,
2018                model_fn=None,
2019                model_dir=None,
2020                config=None,
2021                params=None,
2022                use_tpu=True,
2023                train_batch_size=None,
2024                eval_batch_size=None,
2025                predict_batch_size=None,
2026                batch_axis=None,
2027                eval_on_tpu=True,
2028                export_to_tpu=True,
2029                warm_start_from=None):
2030     """Constructs an `TPUEstimator` instance.
2031 
2032     Args:
2033       model_fn: Model function as required by `Estimator` which returns
2034       EstimatorSpec or TPUEstimatorSpec. `training_hooks`, 'evaluation_hooks',
2035       and `prediction_hooks` must not capure any TPU Tensor inside the model_fn.
2036       model_dir: Directory to save model parameters, graph and etc. This can
2037         also be used to load checkpoints from the directory into a estimator to
2038         continue training a previously saved model. If `None`, the model_dir in
2039         `config` will be used if set. If both are set, they must be same. If
2040         both are `None`, a temporary directory will be used.
2041       config: An `tpu_config.RunConfig` configuration object. Cannot be `None`.
2042       params: An optional `dict` of hyper parameters that will be passed into
2043         `input_fn` and `model_fn`.  Keys are names of parameters, values are
2044         basic python types. There are reserved keys for `TPUEstimator`,
2045         including 'batch_size'.
2046       use_tpu: A bool indicating whether TPU support is enabled. Currently,
2047         - TPU training and evaluation respect this bit, but eval_on_tpu can
2048           override execution of eval. See below.
2049         - Predict still happens on CPU.
2050       train_batch_size: An int representing the global training batch size.
2051         TPUEstimator transforms this global batch size to a per-shard batch
2052         size, as params['batch_size'], when calling `input_fn` and `model_fn`.
2053         Cannot be `None` if `use_tpu` is `True`.
2054         Must be divisible by total number of replicas.
2055       eval_batch_size: An int representing evaluation batch size.
2056         Must be divisible by total number of replicas.
2057       predict_batch_size: An int representing the prediction batch size.
2058         Must be divisible by total number of replicas.
2059       batch_axis: A python tuple of int values describing how each tensor
2060         produced by the Estimator `input_fn` should be split across the TPU
2061         compute shards. For example, if your input_fn produced (images, labels)
2062         where the images tensor is in `HWCN` format, your shard dimensions would
2063         be [3, 0], where 3 corresponds to the `N` dimension of your images
2064         Tensor, and 0 corresponds to the dimension along which to split the
2065         labels to match up with the corresponding images. If None is supplied,
2066         and per_host_input_for_training is True, batches will be sharded based
2067         on the major dimension. If tpu_config.per_host_input_for_training is
2068         False or `PER_HOST_V2`, batch_axis is ignored.
2069       eval_on_tpu: If False, evaluation runs on CPU or GPU. In this case, the
2070         model_fn must return `EstimatorSpec` when called with `mode` as `EVAL`.
2071       export_to_tpu: If True, `export_savedmodel()` exports a metagraph for
2072         serving on TPU besides the one on CPU.
2073       warm_start_from: Optional string filepath to a checkpoint or SavedModel to
2074                        warm-start from, or a `tf.estimator.WarmStartSettings`
2075                        object to fully configure warm-starting.  If the string
2076                        filepath is provided instead of a `WarmStartSettings`,
2077                        then all variables are warm-started, and it is assumed
2078                        that vocabularies and Tensor names are unchanged.
2079 
2080     Raises:
2081       ValueError: `params` has reserved keys already.
2082     """
2083     if config is None or not isinstance(config, tpu_config.RunConfig):
2084       raise ValueError(
2085           '`config` must be provided with type `tpu_config.RunConfig`')
2086 
2087     if params is not None and any(k in params for k in _RESERVED_PARAMS_KEYS):
2088       raise ValueError('{} are reserved keys but existed in params {}.'.format(
2089           _RESERVED_PARAMS_KEYS, params))
2090 
2091     if use_tpu:
2092       # Perform some very basic validations. More validations will be found in
2093       # _InternalTPUContext.
2094       if train_batch_size is None:
2095         raise ValueError('`train_batch_size` cannot be `None`')
2096       util_lib.check_positive_integer(train_batch_size, 'train_batch_size')
2097 
2098       if (config.tpu_config.per_host_input_for_training is
2099           tpu_config.InputPipelineConfig.PER_SHARD_V1 and
2100           config.tpu_config.num_cores_per_replica):
2101         raise ValueError(
2102             'Model parallelism only supports per host input for training. '
2103             'Please adjust TPURunconfig.per_host_input_for_training.')
2104 
2105       if eval_batch_size is not None:
2106         util_lib.check_positive_integer(eval_batch_size, 'eval_batch_size')
2107 
2108       if predict_batch_size is not None:
2109         util_lib.check_positive_integer(predict_batch_size,
2110                                         'predict_batch_size')
2111 
2112     # Verifies the model_fn signature according to Estimator framework.
2113     estimator_lib._verify_model_fn_args(model_fn, params)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2114     # We cannot store config and params in this constructor as parent
2115     # constructor might change them, such as assigning a temp dir for
2116     # config.model_dir.
2117     model_function = self._augment_model_fn(model_fn, batch_axis)
2118 
2119     # Overwrite log_step_count_steps to disable TensorLoggingHook and
2120     # StepCounterHook from being created in Estimator. TPUEstimator already
2121     # added equivalent hooks in _augment_model_fn above.
2122     self._log_every_n_steps = config.log_step_count_steps
2123     config = config.replace(log_step_count_steps=None)
2124 
2125     # Passing non-None params as wrapped model_fn has it.
2126     params = params or {}
2127     super(TPUEstimator, self).__init__(
2128         model_fn=model_function,
2129         model_dir=model_dir,
2130         config=config,
2131         params=params,
2132         warm_start_from=warm_start_from)
2133     self._iterations_per_training_loop = (
2134         self._config.tpu_config.iterations_per_loop)
2135 
2136     # All properties passed to _InternalTPUContext are immutable.
2137     # pylint: disable=protected-access
2138     self._ctx = tpu_context._get_tpu_context(
2139         self._config, train_batch_size,
2140         eval_batch_size, predict_batch_size,
2141         use_tpu,
2142         eval_on_tpu)
2143 
2144     self._export_to_tpu = export_to_tpu
2145 
2146     self._is_input_fn_invoked = None
2147     self._rendezvous = {}

2149   def _add_meta_graph_for_mode(self,
2150                                builder,
2151                                input_receiver_fn_map,
2152                                checkpoint_path,
2153                                strip_default_attrs,
2154                                save_variables=True,
2155                                mode=model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT,
2156                                export_tags=None,
2157                                check_variables=True):

2159       raise NotImplementedError(
2160           'TPUEstimator only handles mode PREDICT for exporting '
2161           'when `export_to_tpu` is `True`; '
2162           'got {}.'.format(mode))
2163 
2164     (super(TPUEstimator, self).
2165      _add_meta_graph_for_mode(builder,
2166                               input_receiver_fn_map,
2167                               checkpoint_path,
2168                               strip_default_attrs,
2169                               save_variables,
2170                               mode=mode,
2171                               export_tags=export_tags,
2172                               check_variables=check_variables))
2173

2176                                input_receiver_fn_map[mode]}

2178       mode = _REWRITE_FOR_INFERENCE_MODE

2180       (super(TPUEstimator, self).
2181        _add_meta_graph_for_mode(builder,
2182                                 input_receiver_fn_map,
2183                                 checkpoint_path,
2184                                 strip_default_attrs,
2185                                 save_variables=False,
2186                                 mode=mode,
2187                                 export_tags=export_tags,

2190   def _call_model_fn(self, features, labels, mode, config):
2191     if mode == _REWRITE_FOR_INFERENCE_MODE:
2192       return self._call_model_fn_for_inference(features, labels, mode, config)
2193     else:
2194       return super(TPUEstimator, self)._call_model_fn(
2195           features, labels, mode, config)
2196 
2197   def _call_model_fn_for_inference(self, features, labels, mode, config):
2198     """Wraps `_call_model_fn` for `export_savedmodel`."""
2199     if mode != _REWRITE_FOR_INFERENCE_MODE:
2200       raise ValueError('mode must be {}; '
2201                        'got {}.'.format(_REWRITE_FOR_INFERENCE_MODE, mode))
2202 
2203     capture = _CapturedObject()
2204 
2205     def computation():
2206       """Compute tpu tensors used in export_outputs.
2207 
2208       Passed to rewrite_for_inference so that model_fn will be called under
2209       the rewriting contexts. Only tpu tensors are returned, but export_outputs
2210       and scaffold are captured.
2211 
2212       Returns:
2213          A list of Tensors used in export_outputs and not marked for
2214          outside_compilation.
2215       """
2216       # We should only call model fn once and it should be inside `computation`
2217       # so that building the graph will happen under `rewrite_for_inference`.
2218       mode = model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT
2219       estimator_spec = self._call_model_fn(features, labels, mode, config)
2220 
2221       # We pick the TPU tensors out from `export_output` and later return them
2222       # from `computation` for rewriting.
2223       tensors_dict = collections.OrderedDict(
2224           (k, _export_output_to_tensors(v))
2225           for k, v in six.iteritems(estimator_spec.export_outputs)
2226       )
2227       tensors = nest.flatten(tensors_dict)
2228       tpu_tensors = [t for t in tensors if _is_tpu_tensor(t)]
2229 
2230       # We cannot return anything other than `tpu_tensors` here so we capture
2231       # the rest for later use.
2232       capture.capture((estimator_spec, tensors_dict, tensors))
2233       return tpu_tensors
2234 
2235     tpu_tensors_on_cpu = tpu.rewrite_for_inference(computation)
2236     estimator_spec, tensors_dict, tensors = capture.get()
2237 
2238     # Reconstruct `tensors`, but with `tpu_tensors` replaced with
2239     # `tpu_tensors_on_cpu`.
2240     new_tensors = []
2241     for t in tensors:
2242       if _is_tpu_tensor(t):
2243         new_tensors.append(tpu_tensors_on_cpu.pop(0))
2244       elif t is None:
2245         new_tensors.append(None)
2246       else:
2247         # Only fetching `tpu_tensors_on_cpu` does not trigger
2248         # TPU computation and blocks, so we add the control dependency here.
2249         control_inputs = (tpu_tensors_on_cpu
2250                           if isinstance(tpu_tensors_on_cpu, (list, tuple))
2251                           else (tpu_tensors_on_cpu,))
2252         with ops.control_dependencies(control_inputs):
2253           new_tensors.append(array_ops.identity(t))
2254 
2255     # Reconstruct `tensors_dict`.
2256     new_tensors_dict = nest.pack_sequence_as(tensors_dict, new_tensors)
2257     # Reconstruct `export_outputs`.
2258     export_outputs = estimator_spec.export_outputs
2259     new_export_outputs = collections.OrderedDict(
2260         (k, _clone_export_output_with_tensors(export_outputs[k], v))
2261         for k, v in six.iteritems(new_tensors_dict)
2262     )
2263 
2264     return estimator_spec._replace(export_outputs=new_export_outputs)
2265 
2266   def _create_global_step(self, graph):
2267     """Creates a global step suitable for TPUs.
2268 
2269     Args:
2270       graph: The graph in which to create the global step.
2271 
2272     Returns:
2273       A global step `Tensor`.
2274 
2275     Raises:
2276       ValueError: if the global step tensor is already defined.
2277     """
2278     return _create_global_step(graph)

2280   def _convert_train_steps_to_hooks(self, steps, max_steps):
2281     with self._ctx.with_mode(model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.TRAIN) as ctx:
2282       if ctx.is_running_on_cpu():
2283         return super(TPUEstimator, self)._convert_train_steps_to_hooks(
2284             steps, max_steps)
2285 
2286     # On TPU.
2287     if steps is None and max_steps is None:
2288       raise ValueError(
2289           'For TPU training, one of `steps` or `max_steps` must be set. '
2290           'Cannot be both `None`.')
2291 
2292     # Estimator.train has explicit positiveness check.
2293     if steps is not None:
2294       util_lib.check_positive_integer(steps, 'Train steps')
2295     if max_steps is not None:
2296       util_lib.check_positive_integer(max_steps, 'Train max_steps')
2297 
2298     return [
2299         _TPUStopAtStepHook(self._iterations_per_training_loop, steps, max_steps)
2300     ]
2301 
2302   def _convert_eval_steps_to_hooks(self, steps):
2303     with self._ctx.with_mode(model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.EVAL) as ctx:
2304       if ctx.is_running_on_cpu():
2305         return super(TPUEstimator, self)._convert_eval_steps_to_hooks(steps)
2306 
2307     if steps is None:
2308       raise ValueError('Evaluate `steps` must be set on TPU. Cannot be `None`.')
2309 
2310     util_lib.check_positive_integer(steps, 'Eval steps')
2311 
2312     return [
2313         evaluation._StopAfterNEvalsHook(  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2314             num_evals=steps),
2315         _SetEvalIterationsHook(steps)
2316     ]

2318   def _call_input_fn(self, input_fn, mode):
2319     """Calls the input function.
2320 
2321     Args:
2322       input_fn: The input function.
2323       mode: ModeKeys
2324 
2325     Returns:
2326       Either features or (features, labels) where features and labels are:
2327         features - `Tensor` or dictionary of string feature name to `Tensor`.
2328         labels - `Tensor` or dictionary of `Tensor` with labels.
2329 
2330     Raises:
2331       ValueError: if input_fn takes invalid arguments or does not have `params`.
2332     """
2333     input_fn_args = function_utils.fn_args(input_fn)
2334     config = self.config  # a deep copy.
2335     kwargs = {}
2336     if 'params' in input_fn_args:
2337       kwargs['params'] = self.params  # a deep copy.
2338     else:
2339       raise ValueError('input_fn ({}) does not include params argument, '
2340                        'required by TPUEstimator to pass batch size as '
2341                        'params["batch_size"]'.format(input_fn))
2342     if 'config' in input_fn_args:
2343       kwargs['config'] = config
2344 
2345     if 'mode' in input_fn_args:
2346       kwargs['mode'] = mode
2347 
2348     # Records the fact input_fn has been invoked.
2349     self._is_input_fn_invoked = True
2350 
2351     with self._ctx.with_mode(mode) as ctx:
2352       # Setting the batch size in params first. This helps user to have same
2353       # input_fn for use_tpu=True/False.
2354       batch_size_for_input_fn = ctx.batch_size_for_input_fn
2355       if batch_size_for_input_fn is not None:
2356         _add_item_to_params(kwargs['params'],
2357                             _BATCH_SIZE_KEY, batch_size_for_input_fn)
2358 
2359       # For export_savedmodel, input_fn is never passed to Estimator. So,
2360       # `is_export_mode` must be False.
2361       if ctx.is_running_on_cpu(is_export_mode=False):
2362         with ops.device('/device:CPU:0'):
2363           return input_fn(**kwargs)
2364 
2365       # For TPU computation, input_fn should be invoked in a tf.while_loop for
2366       # performance. While constructing the tf.while_loop, the structure of
2367       # inputs returned by the `input_fn` needs to be recorded. The structure
2368       # includes whether features or labels is dict or single Tensor, dict keys,
2369       # tensor shapes, and dtypes. The recorded structure is used to create the
2370       # infeed dequeue ops, which must be wrapped and passed as a Fn, called
2371       # inside the TPU computation, as the TPU computation is wrapped inside a
2372       # tf.while_loop also. So, we either pass input_fn to model_fn or pass
2373       # dequeue_fn to model_fn. Here, `input_fn` is passed directly as
2374       # `features` in `model_fn` signature.
2375       def _input_fn(ctx):
2376         _add_item_to_params(kwargs['params'], _CTX_KEY, ctx)
2377         return input_fn(**kwargs)
2378 
2379       return _input_fn
2380

2385     has stronger check. Parent class's check generates confusing warning msg.
2386 
2387     Args:
2388       result: `features` returned by input_fn.
2389     """
2390     pass

2392   def train(self,
2393             input_fn,
2394             hooks=None,
2395             steps=None,
2396             max_steps=None,
2397             saving_listeners=None):
2398     rendezvous = error_handling.ErrorRendezvous(num_sources=3)
2399     self._rendezvous[model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.TRAIN] = rendezvous
2400     try:
2401       return super(TPUEstimator, self).train(
2402           input_fn=input_fn, hooks=hooks, steps=steps, max_steps=max_steps,
2403           saving_listeners=saving_listeners
2404       )
2405     except Exception:  # pylint: disable=broad-except
2406       rendezvous.record_error('training_loop', sys.exc_info())
2407     finally:
2408       rendezvous.record_done('training_loop')
2409       rendezvous.raise_errors()
2410 
2411   def evaluate(self, input_fn, steps=None, hooks=None, checkpoint_path=None,
2412                name=None):
2413     rendezvous = error_handling.ErrorRendezvous(num_sources=3)
2414     self._rendezvous[model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.EVAL] = rendezvous
2415     try:
2416       return super(TPUEstimator, self).evaluate(
2417           input_fn, steps=steps, hooks=hooks, checkpoint_path=checkpoint_path,
2418           name=name
2419       )
2420     except Exception:  # pylint: disable=broad-except
2421       rendezvous.record_error('evaluation_loop', sys.exc_info())
2422     finally:
2423       rendezvous.record_done('evaluation_loop')
2424       rendezvous.raise_errors()
2425 
2426   def predict(self,
2427               input_fn,
2428               predict_keys=None,
2429               hooks=None,
2430               checkpoint_path=None,
2431               yield_single_examples=True):
2432     rendezvous = error_handling.ErrorRendezvous(num_sources=3)
2433     self._rendezvous[model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT] = rendezvous
2434     try:
2435       for result in super(TPUEstimator, self).predict(
2436           input_fn=input_fn,
2437           predict_keys=predict_keys,
2438           hooks=hooks,
2439           checkpoint_path=checkpoint_path,
2440           yield_single_examples=yield_single_examples):
2441         yield result
2442     except Exception:  # pylint: disable=broad-except
2443       rendezvous.record_error('prediction_loop', sys.exc_info())
2444     finally:
2445       rendezvous.record_done('prediction_loop')
2446       rendezvous.raise_errors()
2447 
2448     rendezvous.record_done('prediction_loop')
2449     rendezvous.raise_errors()

2451   def _augment_model_fn(self, model_fn, batch_axis):
2452     """Returns a new model_fn, which wraps the TPU support."""
2453 
2454     def _model_fn(features, labels, mode, config, params):
2455       """A Estimator `model_fn` for TPUEstimator."""
2456       with self._ctx.with_mode(mode) as ctx:
2457         model_fn_wrapper = _ModelFnWrapper(model_fn, config, params, ctx)
2458 
2459         # `input_fn` is called in `train()`, `evaluate()`, and `predict()`,
2460         # but not in `export_savedmodel()`.
2461         if self._is_input_fn_invoked:
2462           is_export_mode = False
2463         else:
2464           is_export_mode = True
2465 
2466         # Clear the bit.
2467         self._is_input_fn_invoked = None
2468 
2469         # examples_hook is added to training_hooks for both CPU and TPU
2470         # execution.
2471         examples_hook = ExamplesPerSecondHook(
2472             ctx.global_batch_size,
2473             output_dir=self.model_dir,
2474             every_n_steps=self._log_every_n_steps)
2475 
2476         if ctx.is_running_on_cpu(is_export_mode=is_export_mode):
2477           logging.info('Running %s on CPU', mode)
2478           estimator_spec = model_fn_wrapper.call_without_tpu(
2479               features, labels, is_export_mode=is_export_mode)
2480           estimator_spec = estimator_spec._replace(
2481               training_hooks=estimator_spec.training_hooks + (examples_hook,))
2482           return estimator_spec
2483 
2484         assert labels is None, '`labels` passed to `model_fn` must be `None`.'
2485         # TPUEstimator._call_input_fn passes `input_fn` as features to here.
2486         assert callable(features), '`input_fn` is not callable.'
2487         input_fn = features
2488 
2489         input_holders = _InputPipeline(input_fn, batch_axis, ctx)
2490         enqueue_ops, dequeue_fn, input_hooks, run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator = (
2491             input_holders.generate_infeed_enqueue_ops_and_dequeue_fn())
2492 
2493         graph = ops.get_default_graph()
2494         for enqueue_op in enqueue_ops:
2495           if isinstance(enqueue_op, list):
2496             graph.get_collection_ref(_TPU_ENQUEUE_OPS).extend(enqueue_op)
2497           else:
2498             graph.add_to_collection(_TPU_ENQUEUE_OPS, enqueue_op)
2499 
2500         if mode == model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.TRAIN:
2501           loss, host_call, scaffold, training_hooks = (
2502               _train_on_tpu_system(ctx, model_fn_wrapper, dequeue_fn))
2503           host_ops = host_call.create_tpu_hostcall()
2504           if host_ops is None:
2505             host_ops = []
2506 
2507           shutdown_hooks = []
2508           shutdown_mode = os.environ.get('TF_TPU_GRACEFUL_SHUTDOWN_MODE',
2509                                          'shutdown_worker')
2510           if shutdown_mode:
2511             if shutdown_mode == 'shutdown_worker':
2512               finalizer_hooks = [
2513                   session_support.ShutdownLameWorkers(timeout_ms=60*1000),
2514               ]
2515             elif shutdown_mode == 'shutdown_computation':
2516               finalizer_hooks = [
2517                   session_support.RestartComputation(timeout_ms=60*1000),
2518               ]
2519             else:
2520               raise ValueError('Unknown TF_TPU_GRACEFUL_SHUTDOWN_MODE "%s"' %
2521                                shutdown_mode)
2522 
2523             shutdown_hooks.append(session_support.GracefulShutdownHook(
2524                 checkpoint_prefix=self.model_dir + '/model.ckpt',
2525                 on_shutdown_hooks=finalizer_hooks
2526             ))
2527 
2528           with ops.control_dependencies([loss]):
2529             global_step = array_ops.identity(training.get_global_step())
2530           hooks = input_hooks + shutdown_hooks
2531           logging_hook_frequency = (    # Divide and round up
2532               (self._log_every_n_steps +
2533                self._config.tpu_config.iterations_per_loop - 1) //
2534               self._config.tpu_config.iterations_per_loop)
2535           hooks.extend([
2536               TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHook(
2537                   ctx,
2538                   enqueue_ops,
2539                   host_ops,
2540                   run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator=(
2541                       run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator),
2542                   rendezvous=self._rendezvous[mode],
2543               ),
2544               InstallSignalHandlerHook(),
2545               training.LoggingTensorHook(
2546                   {
2547                       'loss': array_ops.identity(loss),
2548                       'step': global_step,
2549                   },
2550                   every_n_iter=logging_hook_frequency)
2551           ])
2552           examples_hook._set_steps_per_run(   # pylint: disable=protected-access
2553               self._config.tpu_config.iterations_per_loop)
2554           hooks.append(examples_hook)
2555 
2556           if training_hooks:
2557             hooks.extend(training_hooks)
2558 
2559           chief_hooks = []
2560           if (self._config.save_checkpoints_secs or
2561               self._config.save_checkpoints_steps):
2562             checkpoint_hook = training.CheckpointSaverHook(
2563                 self.model_dir,
2564                 save_secs=self._config.save_checkpoints_secs,
2565                 save_steps=self._config.save_checkpoints_steps,
2566                 scaffold=scaffold)
2567             checkpoint_hook._set_steps_per_run(   # pylint: disable=protected-access
2568                 self._config.tpu_config.iterations_per_loop)
2569             chief_hooks.append(checkpoint_hook)
2570 
2571           summary.scalar(model_fn_lib.LOSS_METRIC_KEY, loss)
2572           with ops.control_dependencies([loss]):
2573             update_ops = _sync_variables_ops()
2574 
2575           # Validate the TPU training graph to catch basic errors
2576           _validate_tpu_training_graph()
2577 
2578           train_op = control_flow_ops.group(*update_ops)
2579           graph.add_to_collection(_TPU_TRAIN_OP, train_op)
2580 
2581           return model_fn_lib.EstimatorSpec(
2582               mode,
2583               loss=loss,
2584               training_chief_hooks=chief_hooks,
2585               training_hooks=hooks,
2586               train_op=train_op,
2587               scaffold=scaffold)
2588 
2589         if mode == model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.EVAL:
2590           total_loss, host_calls, scaffold, eval_hooks = _eval_on_tpu_system(
2591               ctx, model_fn_wrapper, dequeue_fn)
2592           iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
2593           mean_loss = math_ops.div(total_loss,
2594                                    math_ops.cast(
2595                                        iterations_per_loop_var,
2596                                        dtype=total_loss.dtype))
2597 
2598           # Creates a dummy metric update_op for all metrics. Estimator expects
2599           # all metrics in eval_metric_ops have update_op and calls them one by
2600           # one. The real metric update_ops are invoked in a separated thread.
2601           # So, here give Estimator the dummy op for all metrics.
2602           with ops.control_dependencies([mean_loss]):
2603             # After TPU evaluation computation is done (the mean_loss tensor),
2604             # reads all variables back from TPU and updates the eval step
2605             # counter properly
2606             internal_ops_to_run = _sync_variables_ops()
2607             internal_ops_to_run.append(
2608                 _increase_eval_step_op(iterations_per_loop_var))
2609             with ops.control_dependencies(internal_ops_to_run):
2610               dummy_update_op = control_flow_ops.no_op()
2611 
2612           host_call_ret = host_calls.create_tpu_hostcall()
2613           eval_metric_ops = {}
2614           eval_update_ops = []
2615 
2616           for k, v in host_call_ret.get('eval_metrics', {}).items():
2617             eval_metric_ops[k] = (v[0], dummy_update_op)
2618             eval_update_ops.append(v[1])
2619 
2620           if 'host_call' not in host_call_ret:
2621             host_ops = []
2622           else:
2623             host_ops = host_call_ret['host_call']
2624           hooks = [
2625               TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHook(
2626                   ctx,
2627                   enqueue_ops,
2628                   eval_update_ops + host_ops,
2629                   run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator=(
2630                       run_infeed_loop_on_coordinator),
2631                   rendezvous=self._rendezvous[mode]),
2632           ] + input_hooks
2633 
2634           if eval_hooks:
2635             hooks.extend(eval_hooks)
2636 
2637           return model_fn_lib.EstimatorSpec(
2638               mode,
2639               loss=mean_loss,
2640               evaluation_hooks=hooks,
2641               eval_metric_ops=eval_metric_ops,
2642               scaffold=scaffold)
2643 
2644         # Predict
2645         assert mode == model_fn_lib.ModeKeys.PREDICT
2646 
2647         (dummy_predict_op, host_calls,
2648          scaffold, prediction_hooks) = _predict_on_tpu_system(
2649              ctx, model_fn_wrapper, dequeue_fn)
2650         with ops.control_dependencies([dummy_predict_op]):
2651           internal_ops_to_run = _sync_variables_ops()
2652           with ops.control_dependencies(internal_ops_to_run):
2653             dummy_predict_op = control_flow_ops.no_op()
2654 
2655         # In train and evaluation, the main TPU program is passed to monitored
2656         # training session to run. Infeed enqueue and outfeed dequeue are
2657         # executed in side threads. This is not the configuration for
2658         # prediction mode.
2659         #
2660         # For prediction, the Estimator executes the EstimatorSpec.predictions
2661         # directly and yield the element (via generator) to call site. So, the
2662         # outfeed based prediction must be passed to MonitoredSession directly.
2663         # Other parts of the TPU execution are organized as follows.
2664         #
2665         # 1. All outfeed based Tensors must be grouped with predictions Tensors
2666         #    to form a single invocation. This avoid the issue we might trigger
2667         #    multiple outfeeds incorrectly. To achieve this, `host_call` is
2668         #    placed in control_dependencies of `stopping_signals`, and
2669         #    `stopping_signals` is passed into _StoppingPredictHook, which sets
2670         #    the `stopping_signals` as SessionRunArgs. MonitoredSession merges
2671         #    all SessionRunArgs with the fetch in session.run together.
2672         #
2673         # 2. The TPU program (dummy_predict_op) and enqueue_ops (infeed Enqueue)
2674         #    are grouped together. They will be launched once and only once in
2675         #    side threads and they quit naturally according to the SAME stopping
2676         #    condition.
2677         enqueue_ops.append(dummy_predict_op)
2678 
2679         host_call_ret = host_calls.create_tpu_hostcall()
2680         if 'host_call' not in host_call_ret:
2681           host_ops = []
2682         else:
2683           host_ops = host_call_ret['host_call']
2684 
2685         predictions = host_call_ret['predictions']
2686         _verify_cross_hosts_transfer_size(
2687             predictions, message=(
2688                 'The estimated size for TPUEstimatorSpec.predictions is too '
2689                 'large.'))
2690         signals = host_call_ret['signals']
2691 
2692         with ops.control_dependencies(host_ops):
2693           host_ops = []  # Empty, we do do not need it anymore.
2694           scalar_stopping_signal = _StopSignals.as_scalar_stopping_signal(
2695               signals)
2696           predictions = _PaddingSignals.slice_tensor_or_dict(
2697               predictions, signals)
2698 
2699         hooks = [
2700             _StoppingPredictHook(scalar_stopping_signal),
2701             TPUInfeedOutfeedSessionHookForPrediction(
2702                 ctx, enqueue_ops, host_ops, rendezvous=self._rendezvous[mode]),
2703         ] + input_hooks
2704 
2705         if prediction_hooks:
2706           hooks.extend(prediction_hooks)
2707 
2708         return model_fn_lib.EstimatorSpec(
2709             mode,
2710             prediction_hooks=hooks,
2711             predictions=predictions,
2712             scaffold=scaffold)
2713 
2714     return _model_fn
2715

2717 def _is_tpu_tensor(tensor):
2718   if not isinstance(tensor, ops.Tensor):
2719     return False
2720   try:
2721     tensor.op.get_attr(tpu._OUTSIDE_COMPILATION_ATTR)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2722   except ValueError:
2723     return True
2724   else:
2725     return False

2728 def _export_output_to_tensors(export_output):
2729   """Get a list of `Tensors` used in `export_output`.
2730 
2731   Args:
2732     export_output: an `ExportOutput` object such as `ClassificationOutput`,
2733             `RegressionOutput`, or `PredictOutput`.
2734   Returns:
2735     a list of tensors used in export_output.
2736 
2737   Raises:
2738     ValueError: if `export_output` is not one of `ClassificationOutput`,
2739         `RegressionOutput`, or `PredictOutput`.
2740   """
2741   if isinstance(export_output, export_output_lib.ClassificationOutput):
2742     return [export_output.scores, export_output.classes]
2743   elif isinstance(export_output, export_output_lib.RegressionOutput):
2744     return [export_output.value]
2745   elif isinstance(export_output, export_output_lib.PredictOutput):
2746     return export_output.outputs.values()
2747   else:
2748     raise ValueError(
2749         '`export_output` must be have type `ClassificationOutput`, '
2750         '`RegressionOutput`, or `PredictOutput`; got {}.'.format(export_output))
2751 
2752 
2753 def _clone_export_output_with_tensors(export_output, tensors):
2754   """Clones `export_output` but with new `tensors`.
2755 
2756   Args:
2757     export_output: an `ExportOutput` object such as `ClassificationOutput`,
2758             `RegressionOutput`, or `PredictOutput`.
2759     tensors: a list of `Tensors` used to construct a new `export_output`.
2760 
2761   Returns:
2762     A dict similar to `export_output` but with `tensors`.
2763 
2764   Raises:
2765     ValueError: if `export_output` is not one of `ClassificationOutput`,
2766         `RegressionOutput`, or `PredictOutput`.
2767   """
2768   if isinstance(export_output, export_output_lib.ClassificationOutput):
2769     if len(tensors) != 2:
2770       raise ValueError('tensors must be of length 2; '
2771                        'got {}.'.format(len(tensors)))
2772     return export_output_lib.ClassificationOutput(*tensors)
2773   elif isinstance(export_output, export_output_lib.RegressionOutput):
2774     if len(tensors) != 1:
2775       raise ValueError('tensors must be of length 1; '
2776                        'got {}'.format(len(tensors)))
2777     return export_output_lib.RegressionOutput(*tensors)
2778   elif isinstance(export_output, export_output_lib.PredictOutput):
2779     return export_output_lib.PredictOutput(
2780         dict(zip(export_output.outputs.keys(), tensors)))
2781   else:
2782     raise ValueError(
2783         '`export_output` must be have type `ClassificationOutput`, '
2784         '`RegressionOutput`, or `PredictOutput`; got {}.'.format(export_output))

2787 def _eval_on_tpu_system(ctx, model_fn_wrapper, dequeue_fn):
2788   """Executes `model_fn_wrapper` multiple times on all TPU shards."""
2789   iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
2790 
2791   (single_tpu_eval_step, host_calls, captured_scaffold_fn, captured_eval_hooks
2792   ) = model_fn_wrapper.convert_to_single_tpu_eval_step(dequeue_fn)
2793 
2794   def multi_tpu_eval_steps_on_single_shard():
2795     return training_loop.repeat(
2796         iterations_per_loop_var,
2797         single_tpu_eval_step, [_ZERO_LOSS])
2798 
2799   (loss,) = tpu.shard(
2800       multi_tpu_eval_steps_on_single_shard,
2801       inputs=[],
2802       num_shards=ctx.num_replicas,
2803       outputs_from_all_shards=False,
2804       device_assignment=ctx.device_assignment)
2805 
2806   scaffold = _get_scaffold(captured_scaffold_fn)
2807   return loss, host_calls, scaffold, captured_eval_hooks.get()
2808

2810 def _train_on_tpu_system(ctx, model_fn_wrapper, dequeue_fn):
2811   """Executes `model_fn_wrapper` multiple times on all TPU shards."""
2812   iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
2813 
2814   (single_tpu_train_step, host_call, captured_scaffold_fn,
2815    captured_training_hooks) = (
2816        model_fn_wrapper.convert_to_single_tpu_train_step(dequeue_fn))
2817 
2818   def multi_tpu_train_steps_on_single_shard():
2819     return training_loop.repeat(
2820         iterations_per_loop_var,
2821         single_tpu_train_step, [_INITIAL_LOSS])
2822 
2823   (loss,) = tpu.shard(
2824       multi_tpu_train_steps_on_single_shard,
2825       inputs=[],
2826       num_shards=ctx.num_replicas,
2827       outputs_from_all_shards=False,
2828       device_assignment=ctx.device_assignment)
2829 
2830   scaffold = _get_scaffold(captured_scaffold_fn)
2831   return loss, host_call, scaffold, captured_training_hooks.get()
2832 
2833 
2834 def _predict_on_tpu_system(ctx, model_fn_wrapper, dequeue_fn):
2835   """Executes `model_fn_wrapper` multiple times on all TPU shards."""
2836   (single_tpu_predict_step, host_calls, captured_scaffold_fn,
2837    captured_predict_hooks
2838   ) = model_fn_wrapper.convert_to_single_tpu_predict_step(dequeue_fn)
2839 
2840   def multi_tpu_predict_steps_on_single_shard():
2841 
2842     def cond(scalar_stopping_signal):
2843       return math_ops.logical_not(
2844           _StopSignals.should_stop(scalar_stopping_signal))
2845 
2846     inputs = [_StopSignals.NON_STOPPING_SIGNAL]
2847     outputs = training_loop.while_loop(
2848         cond, single_tpu_predict_step, inputs=inputs, name=b'loop')
2849     return outputs
2850 
2851   (dummy_predict_op,) = tpu.shard(
2852       multi_tpu_predict_steps_on_single_shard,
2853       inputs=[],
2854       num_shards=ctx.num_replicas,
2855       outputs_from_all_shards=False,
2856       device_assignment=ctx.device_assignment)
2857 
2858   scaffold = _get_scaffold(captured_scaffold_fn)
2859   return dummy_predict_op, host_calls, scaffold, captured_predict_hooks.get()

2862 def _wrap_computation_in_while_loop(device, op_fn):
2863   """Wraps the ops generated by `op_fn` in tf.while_loop."""
2864 
2865   def computation(i):
2866     with ops.control_dependencies(op_fn()):
2867       return i + 1
2868 
2869   iterations_per_loop_var = _create_or_get_iterations_per_loop()
2870   # By setting parallel_iterations=1, the parallel execution in while_loop is
2871   # basically turned off.
2872   with ops.device(device):
2873     iterations = array_ops.identity(iterations_per_loop_var)
2874     return control_flow_ops.while_loop(
2875         lambda i: i < iterations,
2876         computation, [constant_op.constant(0)],
2877         parallel_iterations=1)
2878 
2879 
2880 def _wrap_computation_in_while_loop_with_stopping_signals(device, op_fn):
2881   """Wraps the ops generated by `op_fn` in tf.while_loop."""
2882 
2883   def cond(scalar_stopping_signal):
2884     return math_ops.logical_not(
2885         _StopSignals.should_stop(scalar_stopping_signal))
2886 
2887   def computation(unused_scalar_stopping_signal):
2888     return_value = op_fn()
2889     execute_ops = return_value['ops']
2890     signals = return_value['signals']
2891     with ops.control_dependencies(execute_ops):
2892       return _StopSignals.as_scalar_stopping_signal(signals)
2893 
2894   # By setting parallel_iterations=1, the parallel execution in while_loop is
2895   # basically turned off.
2896   with ops.device(device):
2897     return control_flow_ops.while_loop(
2898         cond,
2899         computation, [_StopSignals.NON_STOPPING_SIGNAL],
2900         parallel_iterations=1)

2903 def _validate_tpu_training_graph():
2904   """Validate graph before running distributed training.
2905 
2906   Raises:
2907     ValueError: If the graph seems invalid for running on device
2908   """
2909   operations = ops.get_default_graph().get_operations()
2910 
2911   # Check if there is atleast one CrossReplicaSum operation in the graph
2912   # This should be introduced by using the CrossShardOptimizer wrapper
2913   cross_replica_sum_ops = [
2914       o for o in operations if o.type == _CROSS_REPLICA_SUM_OP
2915   ]
2916   if not cross_replica_sum_ops:
2917     raise ValueError(
2918         'CrossShardOptimizer must be used for model training on TPUs.')

2921 class _CapturedObject(object):
2922   """A placeholder to capture an object.
2923 
2924   This is useful when we need to capture a Python object in the Tensorflow
2925   control flow body function and use it outside the control flow.
2926   """
2927 
2928   def __init__(self):
2929     self._object = None
2930     self._captured = False
2931 
2932   def capture(self, o):
2933     if self._captured:
2934       raise RuntimeError(
2935           'InternalError: Object can capture only once. Please file bug.')
2936 
2937     self._captured = True
2938     self._object = o
2939 
2940   def get(self):
2941     if not self._captured:
2942       raise RuntimeError(
2943           'InternalError: Object is not captured properly before `get`. '
2944           'Please file bug.')
2945     return self._object
2946 
2947 
2948 def _get_scaffold(captured_scaffold_fn):
2949   """Retrieves the Scaffold from `captured_scaffold_fn`."""
2950   with _CapturingContext(message='Inside scaffold_fn'):
2951     scaffold_fn = captured_scaffold_fn.get()
2952     if scaffold_fn:
2953       scaffold = scaffold_fn()
2954       if scaffold is None:
2955         raise ValueError(
2956             'TPUEstimatorSpec.scaffold_fn returns None, which is not allowed')
2957     else:
2958       scaffold = None
2959 
2960   if scaffold:
2961     wrapped_finalize = scaffold.finalize
2962 
2963     def _finalize():
2964       with _CapturingContext('Inside Scaffold.finalize'):
2965         wrapped_finalize()
2966 
2967     scaffold.finalize = _finalize
2968   return scaffold
2969

2971 class _CapturingContext(control_flow_ops.ControlFlowContext):
2972   """Tracks references to Tensors defined in TPU replication."""
2973 
2974   def __init__(self, message):
2975     control_flow_ops.ControlFlowContext.__init__(self)
2976     self._message = message
2977 
2978   def AddOp(self, op):  # pylint: disable=invalid-name
2979     for c in op.inputs:
2980       if tpu._TPU_REPLICATE_ATTR in c.op.node_def.attr:  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2981         raise ValueError('{}: Op {} depends on TPU computation {}, '
2982                          'which is not allowed.'.format(self._message, op, c))
2983 
2984   def __enter__(self):
2985     # pylint: disable=protected-access
2986     self._g = ops.get_default_graph()
2987     self._old = self._g._get_control_flow_context()
2988     self._g._set_control_flow_context(self)
2989     # pylint: enable=protected-access
2990 
2991   def __exit__(self, _, __, ___):  # pylint: disable=invalid-name
2992     self._g._set_control_flow_context(self._old)  # pylint: disable=protected-access

2995 class _Inputs(object):
2996   """A data structure representing the input_fn returned values.
2997 
2998   This also supports the returned value from input_fn as `Dataset`.
2999   """
3000 
3001   def __init__(self, features=None, labels=None, dataset=None, signals=None):
3002     if dataset is not None and (features is not None or labels is not None or
3003                                 signals is not None):
3004       raise RuntimeError('Internal Error: Either (features and labels) or '
3005                          'dataset should be provided, not both. Please file '
3006                          'bug')
3007 
3008     self._features = features
3009     self._labels = labels
3010     self._signals = signals
3011 
3012     self._dataset = dataset
3013     self._iterator = None
3014 
3015   @staticmethod
3016   def from_input_fn(return_values):
3017     """Returns an `_Inputs` instance according to `input_fn` return value."""
3018     if isinstance(return_values, dataset_ops.Dataset):
3019       dataset = return_values
3020       return _Inputs(dataset=dataset)
3021 
3022     features, labels = _Inputs._parse_inputs(return_values)
3023     return _Inputs(features, labels)
3024 
3025   @staticmethod
3026   def _parse_inputs(return_values):
3027     if isinstance(return_values, tuple):
3028       features, labels = return_values
3029     else:
3030       features, labels = return_values, None
3031     return features, labels
3032 
3033   @property
3034   def is_dataset(self):
3035     """Returns True if the return value from input_fn is Dataset."""
3036     return self._dataset is not None
3037 
3038   def dataset_initializer(self):
3039     """Returns the dataset's initializer.
3040 
3041     The initializer must be run before calling `features_and_labels`.
3042     """
3043     self._iterator = self._dataset.make_initializable_iterator()
3044     return self._iterator.initializer
3045 
3046   def features_and_labels(self):
3047     """Gets `features` and `labels`."""
3048     if self.is_dataset:
3049       if self._iterator is None:
3050         raise RuntimeError('Internal error: Must run dataset_initializer '
3051                            'before calling features_and_labels(). Please file '
3052                            'a bug!')
3053       return _Inputs._parse_inputs(self._iterator.get_next())
3054 
3055     return (self._features, self._labels)
3056 
3057   def signals(self):
3058     return self._signals
3059 
3060   @property
3061   def dataset(self):
3062     return self._dataset
3063 
3064 
3065 class _InputsWithStoppingSignals(_Inputs):
3066   """Inputs with `_StopSignals` inserted into the dataset."""
3067 
3068   def __init__(self,
3069                dataset,
3070                batch_size,
3071                add_padding=False,
3072                num_invocations_per_step=1):
3073 
3074     assert dataset is not None
3075     user_provided_dataset = dataset.map(
3076         _InputsWithStoppingSignals.insert_stopping_signal(
3077             stop=False, batch_size=batch_size, add_padding=add_padding))
3078     if num_invocations_per_step == 1:
3079       final_batch_dataset = dataset.take(1).map(
3080           _InputsWithStoppingSignals.insert_stopping_signal(
3081               stop=True, batch_size=batch_size, add_padding=add_padding))
3082     else:
3083       # We append (2 * num_invocations_per_step - 1) batches for exhausting the
3084       # user_provided_dataset and stop properly.
3085       # For example, if num_invocations_per_step is 2, we append 3 additional
3086       # padding batches: b1, b2, b3.
3087       # If user_provided_dataset contains two batches: a1, a2
3088       # Step 1: [a1, a2]
3089       # Step 2: [b1, b2] -> STOP
3090       # If user_provided_dataset contains three batches: a1, a2, a3.
3091       # The training loops:
3092       # Step 1: [a1, a2]
3093       # Step 2: [a3, b1]
3094       # Step 3: [b2, b3] -> STOP.
3095       final_batch_dataset = dataset.take(1).map(
3096           _InputsWithStoppingSignals.insert_stopping_signal(
3097               stop=True, batch_size=batch_size, add_padding=add_padding))
3098       final_batch_dataset = final_batch_dataset.repeat(
3099           2 * num_invocations_per_step - 1)
3100 
3101       def _set_mask(data_dict):
3102         signals = data_dict['signals']
3103         signals['padding_mask'] = array_ops.ones_like(signals['padding_mask'])
3104         data_dict['signals'] = signals
3105         return data_dict
3106 
3107       # Mask out the extra batch.
3108       final_batch_dataset = final_batch_dataset.map(_set_mask)
3109 
3110     dataset = user_provided_dataset.concatenate(final_batch_dataset).prefetch(2)
3111 
3112     super(_InputsWithStoppingSignals, self).__init__(dataset=dataset)
3113     self._current_inputs = None
3114 
3115   def features_and_labels(self):
3116     if self._current_inputs is not None:
3117       raise RuntimeError(
3118           'Internal Error: The previous inputs have not been properly '
3119           'consumed. First call features_and_labels, then call signals.')
3120 
3121     inputs_with_signals = self._iterator.get_next()
3122     features = inputs_with_signals['features']
3123     labels = inputs_with_signals.get('labels')
3124 
3125     self._current_inputs = inputs_with_signals
3126     return features, labels
3127 
3128   def signals(self):
3129     """Returns the `Signals` from `_Inputs`."""
3130     if self._current_inputs is None:
3131       raise RuntimeError(
3132           'Internal Error: The current inputs have not been properly '
3133           'generated. First call features_and_labels, then call signals.')
3134     signals = self._current_inputs['signals']
3135     self._current_inputs = None
3136     return signals
3137 
3138   @staticmethod
3139   def insert_stopping_signal(stop, batch_size, add_padding=False):
3140     """Inserts stopping_signal into dataset via _map_fn.
3141 
3142     Here we change the data structure in the dataset, such that the return value
3143     is a dictionary now and `features`, `labels`, and `signals` are three
3144     distinguished keys in that dict. This provides a better structure, which
3145     eases the process to decompose the inputs (see `features_and_labels`).
3146 
3147     Args:
3148       stop: bool, state of current stopping signals.
3149       batch_size: int, batch size.
3150       add_padding: bool, whether to pad the tensor to full batch size.
3151 
3152     Returns:
3153       A map_fn passed to dataset.map API.
3154     """
3155 
3156     def _map_fn(*args):
3157       """The map fn to insert signals."""
3158       if len(args) == 1:
3159         # Unpack the single Tensor/dict argument as features. This is required
3160         # for the input_fn returns no labels.
3161         args = args[0]
3162       features, labels = _Inputs._parse_inputs(args)
3163       new_input_dict = {}
3164 
3165       if add_padding:
3166         padding_mask, features, labels = (
3167             _PaddingSignals.pad_features_and_labels(
3168                 features, labels, batch_size))
3169 
3170         new_input_dict['features'] = features
3171         if labels is not None:
3172           new_input_dict['labels'] = labels
3173 
3174       else:
3175         new_input_dict['features'] = features
3176         if labels is not None:
3177           new_input_dict['labels'] = labels
3178         padding_mask = None
3179 
3180       new_input_dict['signals'] = _StopSignals(
3181           stop=stop, batch_size=batch_size, padding_mask=padding_mask).as_dict()
3182 
3183       return new_input_dict
3184 
3185     return _map_fn
3186 
3187 
3188 class _StopSignals(object):
3189   """Signals class holding all logic to handle TPU stopping condition."""
3190 
3191   NON_STOPPING_SIGNAL = False
3192   STOPPING_SIGNAL = True
3193 
3194   def __init__(self, stop, batch_size, padding_mask=None):
3195     self._stop = stop
3196     self._batch_size = batch_size
3197     self._padding_mask = padding_mask
3198 
3199   def as_dict(self):
3200     """Returns the signals as Python dict."""
3201     shape = [self._batch_size, 1]
3202     dtype = dtypes.bool
3203 
3204     if self._stop:
3205       stopping = array_ops.ones(shape=shape, dtype=dtype)
3206     else:
3207       stopping = array_ops.zeros(shape=shape, dtype=dtype)
3208 
3209     signals = {'stopping': stopping}
3210     if self._padding_mask is not None:
3211       signals['padding_mask'] = self._padding_mask
3212     return signals
3213 
3214   @staticmethod
3215   def as_scalar_stopping_signal(signals):
3216     return array_ops.identity(signals['stopping'][0][0])
3217 
3218   @staticmethod
3219   def should_stop(scalar_stopping_signal):
3220     """Detects whether scalar_stopping_signal indicates stopping."""
3221     if isinstance(scalar_stopping_signal, ops.Tensor):
3222       # STOPPING_SIGNAL is a constant True. Here, the logical_and is just the TF
3223       # way to express the bool check whether scalar_stopping_signal is True.
3224       return math_ops.logical_and(
3225           scalar_stopping_signal, _StopSignals.STOPPING_SIGNAL)
3226     else:
3227       # For non Tensor case, it is used in SessionRunHook. So, we cannot modify
3228       # the graph anymore. Here, we use pure Python.
3229       return bool(scalar_stopping_signal)
3230 
3231 
3232 class _PaddingSignals(object):
3233   """Signals class holding all logic to handle padding."""
3234 
3235   @staticmethod
3236   def pad_features_and_labels(features, labels, batch_size):
3237     """Pads out the batch dimension of features and labels."""
3238     real_batch_size = array_ops.shape(
3239         _PaddingSignals._find_any_tensor(features))[0]
3240 
3241     batch_size_tensor = constant_op.constant(batch_size, dtypes.int32)
3242 
3243     check_greater = check_ops.assert_greater_equal(
3244         batch_size_tensor, real_batch_size,
3245         data=(batch_size_tensor, real_batch_size),
3246         message='The real batch size should not be greater than batch_size.')
3247 
3248     with ops.control_dependencies([check_greater]):
3249       missing_count = batch_size_tensor - real_batch_size
3250 
3251     def pad_single_tensor(tensor):
3252       """Pads out the batch dimension of a tensor to the complete batch_size."""
3253       rank = len(tensor.shape)
3254       assert rank > 0
3255       padding = array_ops.stack([[0, missing_count]] + [[0, 0]] * (rank - 1))
3256       padded_shape = (batch_size,) + tuple(tensor.shape[1:])
3257       padded_tensor = array_ops.pad(tensor, padding)
3258       padded_tensor.set_shape(padded_shape)
3259       return padded_tensor
3260 
3261     def nest_pad(tensor_or_dict):
3262       return nest.map_structure(pad_single_tensor, tensor_or_dict)
3263 
3264     features = nest_pad(features)
3265     if labels is not None:
3266       labels = nest_pad(labels)
3267 
3268     padding_mask = _PaddingSignals._padding_mask(
3269         real_batch_size, missing_count, batch_size)
3270 
3271     return padding_mask, features, labels
3272 
3273   @staticmethod
3274   def slice_tensor_or_dict(tensor_or_dict, signals):
3275     """Slice the real Tensors according to padding mask in signals."""
3276 
3277     padding_mask = signals['padding_mask']
3278     batch_size = array_ops.shape(padding_mask)[0]
3279 
3280     def verify_batch_size(tensor):
3281       check_batch_size = math_ops.equal(batch_size, tensor.shape[0])
3282       with ops.control_dependencies([check_batch_size]):
3283         return array_ops.identity(tensor)
3284 
3285     def slice_single_tensor(tensor):
3286       rank = len(tensor.shape)
3287       assert rank > 0
3288       real_batch_size = batch_size - math_ops.reduce_sum(padding_mask)
3289       return verify_batch_size(tensor)[0:real_batch_size]
3290 
3291     # As we split the Tensors to all TPU cores and concat them back, it is
3292     # important to ensure the real data is placed before padded ones, i.e.,
3293     # order is preserved. By that, the sliced padding mask should have all 0's.
3294     # If this assertion failed, # the slice logic here would not hold.
3295     sliced_padding_mask = slice_single_tensor(padding_mask)
3296     assert_padding_mask = math_ops.equal(
3297         math_ops.reduce_sum(sliced_padding_mask), 0)
3298 
3299     with ops.control_dependencies([assert_padding_mask]):
3300       should_stop = _StopSignals.should_stop(
3301           _StopSignals.as_scalar_stopping_signal(signals))
3302 
3303     is_full_batch = math_ops.equal(math_ops.reduce_sum(padding_mask), 0)
3304 
3305     def slice_fn(tensor):
3306       # If the current batch is full batch or part of stopping signals, we do
3307       # not need to slice to save performance.
3308       return control_flow_ops.cond(
3309           math_ops.logical_or(should_stop, is_full_batch),
3310           (lambda: verify_batch_size(tensor)),
3311           (lambda: slice_single_tensor(tensor)))
3312 
3313     return nest.map_structure(slice_fn, tensor_or_dict)
3314 
3315   @staticmethod
3316   def _find_any_tensor(batch_features):
3317     tensors = [x for x in nest.flatten(batch_features)
3318                if isinstance(x, ops.Tensor)]
3319     if not tensors:
3320       raise ValueError('Cannot find any Tensor in features dict.')
3321     return tensors[0]
3322 
3323   @staticmethod
3324   def _padding_mask(real_batch_size, missing_count, batch_size):
3325     padding_mask = array_ops.concat(
3326         [
3327             array_ops.zeros((real_batch_size,), dtype=dtypes.int32),
3328             array_ops.ones((missing_count,), dtype=dtypes.int32)
3329         ],
3330         axis=0)
3331     padding_mask.set_shape((batch_size,))
3332     return padding_mask
3333 
3334 
3335 def _verify_cross_hosts_transfer_size(tensor_dict, message):
3336   total_size = 0
3337   tensor_structure = {}
3338   for key, tensor in tensor_dict.items():
3339     shape = tensor.shape
3340     size = np.product(shape) * tensor.dtype.size
3341     tensor_structure[key] = shape
3342     total_size += size
3343   if total_size >= _ONE_GIGABYTE:
3344     raise ValueError(
3345         '{} The transfer size is larger than the protobuf limit. Please '
3346         'consider to use Tensors with smaller shapes or reduce batch '
3347         'size. Given:\n'
3348         '{}'.format(message, '\n'.join([
3349             ' -- Key: {}, Shape: {}'.format(k, v)
3350             for k, v in tensor_structure.items()])))
3351 
3352 
3353 def _add_item_to_params(params, key, value):
3354   """Adds a new item into `params`."""
3355   if isinstance(params, hparam.HParams):
3356     # For HParams, we need to use special API.
3357     if key in params:
3358       params.set_hparam(key, value)
3359     else:
3360       params.add_hparam(key, value)
3361   else:
3362     # Now params is Python dict.
3363     params[key] = value
3364 
3365 
3366 def export_estimator_savedmodel(estimator,
3367                                 export_dir_base,
3368                                 serving_input_receiver_fn,
3369                                 assets_extra=None,
3370                                 as_text=False,
3371                                 checkpoint_path=None,
3372                                 strip_default_attrs=False):
3373   """Export `Estimator` trained model for TPU inference.
3374 
3375   Args:
3376     estimator: `Estimator` with which model has been trained.
3377     export_dir_base: A string containing a directory in which to create
3378       timestamped subdirectories containing exported SavedModels.
3379     serving_input_receiver_fn: A function that takes no argument and
3380       returns a `ServingInputReceiver` or `TensorServingInputReceiver`.
3381     assets_extra: A dict specifying how to populate the assets.extra directory
3382       within the exported SavedModel, or `None` if no extra assets are needed.
3383     as_text: whether to write the SavedModel proto in text format.
3384     checkpoint_path: The checkpoint path to export.  If `None` (the default),
3385       the most recent checkpoint found within the model directory is chosen.
3386     strip_default_attrs: Boolean. If `True`, default-valued attributes will be
3387       removed from the NodeDefs.
3388 
3389   Returns:
3390     The string path to the exported directory.
3391   """
3392   # `TPUEstimator` requires `tpu_config.RunConfig`, so we cannot use
3393   # `estimator.config`.
3394   config = tpu_config.RunConfig(model_dir=estimator.model_dir)
3395   est = TPUEstimator(
3396       estimator._model_fn,  # pylint: disable=protected-access
3397       config=config,
3398       params=estimator.params,
3399       use_tpu=True,
3400       train_batch_size=2048,  # Does not matter.
3401       eval_batch_size=2048,  # Does not matter.
3402   )
3403   return est.export_savedmodel(export_dir_base, serving_input_receiver_fn,
3404                                assets_extra,
3405                                as_text,
3406                                checkpoint_path,
3407                                strip_default_attrs)
